he Alps and is being linked to a growing number of infections around Europe}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Coronavirus spreads in Europe from Italy, first case in Latin America |url=https://www.rnz.co.nz/news/world/410449/coronavirus-spreads-in-europe-from-italy-first-case-in-latin-america |accessdate=30 March 2020 |work=RNZ |date=26 February 2020 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Europe's coronavirus outbreak spreads from Italy |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-51638095 |accessdate=31 March 2020 |work=BBC News |date=26 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Day |first1=Michael |title=Covid-19: Italy confirms 11 deaths as cases spread from north |journal=BMJ |date=26 February 2020 |volume=368 |pages=m757 |doi=10.1136/bmj.m757 |pmid=32102793 |url=https://www.bmj.com/content/368/bmj.m757 |accessdate=30 March 2020 |quote=Confirmed cases of covid-19 in Italy leapt by 45% to reach 322 on 25 February, and four more deaths were confirmed amid signs that the infection was spreading around the country and across borders. ...  Authorities in Austria and Croatia also reported their first cases of covid-19 and said that the patients affected had recently travelled from Italy\u2019s Lombardy region, confirming fears that travellers were starting to carry the infection from its European epicentre. An Italian couple from the north of Italy tested positive on the Spanish island of Tenerife, forcing the quarantine of their hotel.}}</ref>\n\n===Africa===\n'''Algeria''' \u2013 \nOn 25 February 2020, Algeria confirmed its first case, an Italian man from [[Bertonico]], Lombardy who arrived in the country on 17 February.<ref name=\":2\" /><ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.trust.org/item/20200225190135-gnit5/|title=Algeria confirms first case of coronavirus \u2013 state TV|last=Foundation|first=Thomson Reuters|website=news.trust.org|access-date=25 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://africatimes.com/2020/02/25/algerian-health-minister-confirms-first-covid-19-case/|title=Algerian health minister confirms first COVID-19 case {{!}} Africa Times|date=25 February 2020|website=africatimes.com|access-date=25 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''Central African Republic''' \u2013\nOn 14 March, the Central African minister of health announced the first confirmed case in the country, a 74-year-old Italian citizen coming from Milan.<ref>{{cite news |title=RCA: Un premier cas confirm\u00e9 de Coronavirus \u00e0 Bangui \u2013 Radio Ndeke Luka |url=https://www.radiondekeluka.org/actualites/sante/35266-rca-un-premier-cas-confirme-de-coronavirus-en-centrafrique.html |accessdate=15 March 2020 |work=radiondekeluka.org |language=fr-fr}}</ref>\n\n'''C\u00f4te d'Ivoire''' \u2013\nOn Tuesday, 10 March, C\u00f4te d'Ivoire confirmed its first case, a 45-year-old Ivorien male who had sojourned in Italy.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.africanews.com/2020/03/11/ivory-coast-records-first-coronavirus-case/|title=Ivory Coast confirms first coronavirus case|website=Africanews|date=11 March 2020|accessdate=12 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''Morocco''' \u2013\nOn 2 March, the Moroccan Ministry of Health reported its first case, a man who had lived in Italy.<ref>{{cite news |title=Morocco reports first coronavirus case: health ministry |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-morocco/morocco-reports-first-coronavirus-case-health-ministry-idUSKBN20P33T |accessdate=3 March 2020 |agency=Reuters |date=2 March 2020 }}</ref>\n\n'''Nigeria''' \u2013 \nOn 28 February 2020, Nigeria confirmed its first case, an Italian man who tested positive at Lagos University Teaching Hospital and was treated at the Infectious Disease Hospital in [[Yaba, Lagos]]. He entered Nigeria from Milan on 25 February for a brief business visit, then fell ill the next day.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pmnewsnigeria.com/2020/02/28/breaking-deadly-coronavirus-confirmed-in-lagos-nigeria-at-last/|title=Breaking: Deadly Coronavirus confirmed in Lagos Nigeria at last|date=28 February 2020|website=P.M. News|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''Senegal''' \u2013\n[[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Senegal|Senegal]] confirmed on 12 March that their fifth confirmed case was a Senegalese national who returned from Italy on 6 March.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.aa.com.tr/en/africa/senegal-confirms-fifth-case-of-covid-19/1762907|title=Senegal confirms fifth case of COVID-19|website=aa.com.tr|accessdate=13 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''Seychelles''' \u2013\n[[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Seychelles|Seychelles]] confirmed its first two cases on 14 March. Both were people who were in contact with someone in Italy who tested positive.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Bonnelame |first1=Betyme |title=2 Seychellois test positive for COVID-19 as globe-sweeping virus reaches island nation|url=http://www.seychellesnewsagency.com/articles/12593/+Seychellois+test+positive+for+COVID-+as+globe-sweeping+virus+reaches+island+nation |accessdate=14 March 2020 |agency=[[Seychelles News Agency]] |date=14 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''South Africa''' \u2013\n[[2020 coronavirus pandemic in South Africa|South Africa]] confirmed that its first seven cases were South African residents returning from Italy.<ref>{{cite web\n|url=https://www.news24.com/SouthAfrica/News/coronavirus-update-4-more-cases-confirmed-bringing-total-in-sa-to-7-20200309\n|title=Coronavirus update: 4 more cases confirmed, bringing total in SA to 7\n|date=9 March 2020\n|website=News24\n\n|access-date=9 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web\n|url=http://www.nicd.ac.za/third-confirmed-case-of-covid-19-in-south-africa/\n|title=Third confirmed case of COVID-19 in South Africa\n|last1=Mkhize\n|first1=Zwelini\n|date=8 March 2020\n|website=NICD\n\n|access-date=8 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''Tunisia''' \u2013 \nTunisia confirmed its first case on 2 March 2020, and identified the patient as a Tunisian who had returned from Italy.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://punchng.com/italian-returnee-confirmed-tunisias-first-coronavirus-case/|title=Italian returnee confirmed Tunisia's first coronavirus case|accessdate=8 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Americas===\n'''Argentina''' \u2013\nOn 3 March, Argentina confirmed its first case, a 43-year-old man who arrived in Argentina two days earlier after a trip that included northern Italy.<ref>{{cite news |title=Argentine health minister confirms country's first case of coronavirus |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-argentina/argentine-health-minister-confirms-countrys-first-case-of-coronavirus-idUSKBN20Q2SC |accessdate=4 March 2020 |agency=Reuters |date=3 March 2020 }}</ref>\n\n'''Bolivia''' \u2013\nTwo people who returned from Italy to Bolivia were tested positive.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://eldeber.com.bo/169041_confirman-dos-casos-de-coronavirus-en-bolivia|title=Confirman dos casos de coronavirus en Bolivia &#124; EL DEBER|website=eldeber.com.bo|accessdate=11 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''Brazil''' \u2013\nOn 25 February, Brazil confirmed its first case, a 61-year-old man from [[S\u00e3o Paulo]] who travelled to Lombardy between 9 and 21 February. He showed mild symptoms and was quarantined at home.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/sp/sao-paulo/noticia/2020/02/25/ministerio-da-saude-investiga-possivel-paciente-com-coronavirus-em-sp-caso-foi-para-contraprova.ghtml|title=Minist\u00e9rio da Sa\u00fade investiga poss\u00edvel paciente com coronav\u00edrus em SP; caso foi para contraprova|website=G1|language=pt-br|access-date=26 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''Canada''' \u2013\nCases 21 and 27 in Ontario were persons who had travelled to Italy.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/toronto/ontario-confirms-3-new-cases-coronavirus-1.5486670|title=Ontario confirms three new cases of coronavirus, bringing total to 23 in province|date=5 March 2020|website=Toronto|access-date=5 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200221134501/https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/toronto/ontario-confirms-3-new-cases-coronavirus-1.5486670|archive-date=5 March 2020