test after having previously tested negative.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/coronavirus-live-updates-south-korea-reports-476-new-cases-total-at-4212/liveblog/74432985.cms|title=Coronavirus India Live Updates: Italian tests positive for coronavirus in Jaipur|website=The Times of India|access-date=2 March 2020}}</ref> On 3 March, his wife also tested positive.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.businesstoday.in/current/economy-politics/coronavirus-outbreak-case-live-updates-latest-news-covid-19-delhi-noida-agra-india/story/397426.html|title=Coronavirus Live Updates: Italian tourist's wife tests positive, number of cases rises to 7|website=Business Today|date=3 March 2020|access-date=3 March 2020}}</ref>\nOn 4 March 14 more Italian tourists who were kept at a quarantine facility in Delhi were confirmed positive, as well as the group's Indian driver.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/28-confirmed-cases-of-coronavirus-in-india-gom-to-meet-today-health-minister-harsh-vardhan/articleshow/74472369.cms|title=28 confirmed cases of coronavirus in India, GoM to meet today: Health minister Harsh Vardhan|date=4 March 2020|work=The Economic Times|access-date=4 March 2020}}</ref> A [[Paytm]] employee in [[Gurgaon]] who had returned from a vacation in Italy also tested positive.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/coronavirus-covid19-paytm-employee-tests-positive-gurugram-1652475-2020-03-04|title=29th coronavirus case in India: After 15 Italian tourists, Paytm employee tests positive for Covid-19|last=DelhiMarch 4|first=Aishwarya Paliwal New|last2=March 5|first2=2020UPDATED|website=India Today|access-date=8 March 2020|last3=Ist|first3=2020 13:52}}</ref> On 8 March, five members of a family in [[Kerala]] tested positive, three of whom had returned from Italy.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ndtv.com/india-news/5-of-family-infected-with-coronavirus-in-kerala-total-positive-cases-in-india-ris