 in Tokyo\")|language=Japanese|work=Asahi Shimbun|date=13 March 2020|access-date=20 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''Jordan''' \u2013\nOn 2 March, Jordan confirmed that a man in his 30s who had returned from Italy two weeks earlier had tested positive, with other potential cases under observation.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://arab.news/v47zf|title=Jordan announces first coronavirus case from Italy|date=2 March 2020|website=Arab News|access-date=5 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|author=Zehra Nur D\u00fcz |url=https://www.aa.com.tr/en/health/jordan-confirms-first-coronavirus-case/1752064|title=Jordan confirms first coronavirus case|publisher=Anadolu Agency|date=2 March 2020|access-date=5 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''[[Mainland China]]''' \u2013\nOn 1 March, [[Qingtian County]], [[Lishui]], Zhejiang confirmed its first imported case, a 31-year-old Chinese woman who had worked at a restaurant in [[Bergamo]].<ref>{{cite web |script-title=zh:\u4e3d\u6c34\u65b0\u589e1\u4f8b\u610f\u5927\u5229\u8f93\u5165\u6027\u786e\u8bca\u75c5\u4f8b\uff1a31\u5c81\u9752\u7530\u5973\u5b50\u4ece\u610f\u5927\u5229\u5230\u8fbe\u4e0a\u6d77\u6d66\u4e1c\u673a\u573a |url=https://hznews.hangzhou.com.cn/kejiao/content/2020-03/02/content_7686772.htm |language=zh-cn |website=hangzhou.com.cn |date=2 March 2020|access-date=2 March 2020}}</ref> On 2 March, seven more imported cases were confirmed in Qingtian County that are related to the first imported case.<ref>{{cite web |script-title=zh:\u6d59\u6c5f\u9752\u7530\u53bf\u65b0\u589e7\u4f8b\u5883\u5916\u8f93\u5165\u75c5\u4f8b \u66fe\u5728\u610f\u5927\u5229\u540c\u4e00\u9910\u5385\u5de5\u4f5c |url=http://www.bjd.com.cn/a/202003/03/WS5e5dbf81e4b05d1eff0b4301.html|language=zh-cn |work=[[Beijing Daily]] |date=3 March 2020|access-date=3 March 2020}}</ref> Beijing reported one imported case on 3 March, four on 5 March, three on 6 March, one on 7 March and five on March.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://wjw.beijing.gov.cn/xwzx_20031/wnxw/202003/t20200304_1678404.html|script-title=