jav\u00edk]].<ref name=\"ruv.is\">{{cite web|url=https://www.ruv.is/frett/fyrsta-tilfelli-covid-19-greint-a-islandi|title=Fyrsta tilfelli COVID-19 greint \u00e1 \u00cdslandi|date=28 February 2020|website=R\u00daV}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://bnonews.com/index.php/2020/02/the-latest-coronavirus-cases/|title=Tracking coronavirus: Map, data and timeline|first=B. N. O.|last=News|date=18 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mbl.is/frettir/innlent/2020/02/28/fyrsta_tilfelli_koronuveiru_greinist_a_islandi/|title=Fyrsta tilfelli k\u00f3r\u00f3nuveiru greinist \u00e1 \u00cdslandi|website=mbl.is|language=is|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref>\nOn 5 March, a total of 34 cases had been confirmed in Iceland, most of which are imported cases from Italy.\n\n'''Ireland''' \u2013\nOn 27 February 2020, Ireland's first case was confirmed by the [[Health Protection Surveillance Centre]]. The male patient had travelled to an affected region in Northern Italy.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rte.ie/news/coronavirus/2020/0229/1119357-coronavirus-ireland/ |title=First case of Covid-19 diagnosed in east of Ireland |date=1 March 2020 |access-date=4 March 2020 |publisher=Raidi\u00f3 Teilif\u00eds \u00c9ireann }}</ref> A second, unrelated case was confirmed on 3 March, a female in the eastern portion of Ireland who had travelled to Italy.<ref>{{cite web|first1=Paul|last1=Cullen|accessdate=3 March 2020|title=Second case of coronavirus is confirmed in east of Ireland|url=https://www.irishtimes.com/news/health/second-case-of-coronavirus-is-confirmed-in-east-of-ireland-1.4191961|website=The Irish Times}}</ref>\n\n'''Latvia''' \u2013\nOn 2 March, Latvia confirmed its first case, a person who had travelled from Milan to Munich and then to [[Riga]] on 29 February.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://eng.lsm.lv/article/society/health/first-case-of-covid-19-coronavirus-confirmed-in-latvia.a350338/|title=First case of COVID-19 coronavirus confirmed in Latvia|website=lsm.lv|access-date=3 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''Lithuania''' \u2013\nOn 28 February, Lithuania confirmed its first case, a 39-year-old woman who arrived in [[Kaunas]] from [[Verona]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.15min.lt/naujiena/aktualu/lietuva/koronavirusas-pasieke-lietuva-uzfiksuotas-pirmasis-atvejis-56-1282110|title=Lietuvoje patvirtintas pirmasis koronaviruso atvejis \u2013 susirgo 39 met\u0173 moteris, atskridusi \u012f Kaun\u0105|website=15min.lt|language=lt|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''Luxembourg''' \u2013\nThe nation's second and fourth cases were persons who had travelled to Italy.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://5minutes.rtl.lu/actu/luxembourg/a/1479054.html|title=RTL 5minutes \u2013 Il revenait d'Italie: Un deuxi\u00e8me cas de coronavirus confirm\u00e9 au Luxembourg|accessdate=8 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://5minutes.rtl.lu/actu/luxembourg/a/1479918.html|title=Sant\u00e9: Un 4e cas de coronavirus valid\u00e9 au Luxembourg|website=5minutes.rtl.lu|accessdate=8 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''Malta''' \u2013\nA 12-year-old Italian brought the infection to Malta.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/world/covid19-malta-first-coronavirus-case-italian-girl-12512852|title=Italian girl becomes Malta's first coronavirus case|website=CNA|accessdate=8 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''Moldova''' \u2013\nOn 7 March, Moldova confirmed its first case, a 48-year-old woman who had returned from Italy.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deschide.md/ro/stiri/social/62248/BREAKING-NEWS-Primul-caz-de-coronavirus-depistat-%C3%AEn-Republica-Moldova-O-femeie-de-48-de-ani-infectat%C4%83.htm|title=BREAKING NEWS// Primul caz de coronavirus depistat \u00een Republica Moldova. O femeie de 48 de ani, infectat\u0103|trans-title=BREAKING NEWS// First coronavirus case detected in Republic of Moldova. A 48-year-old woman, infected|language=ro|website=Deschide.md|date=7 March 2020|access-date=7 March 2020}}</ref> Moldova confirmed the existence of imported case from diseased Italy on 11 March.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://stiri.md/article/incidente/al-patrulea-caz-de-coronavirus-confirmat-in-r-moldova|title=Al patrulea caz de coronavirus, confirmat \u00een R. Moldova|website=stiri.md|accessdate=13 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''Netherlands''' \u2013\nOn 27 February, the Netherlands confirmed its first case, a man who had been in Lombardy and was admitted to Elisabeth-TweeSteden Hospital in [[Tilburg]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rivm.nl/nieuws/patient-met-nieuw-coronavirus-in-nederland|title=Pati\u00ebnt met nieuw coronavirus in Nederland {{!}} RIVM|website=www.rivm.nl|access-date=1 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.telegraaf.nl/nieuws/214089776/rivm-eerste-coronageval-in-nederland|title=RIVM: eerste coronageval in Nederland|date=27 February 2020|website=De Telegraaf|language=nl|access-date=1 March 2020}}</ref>\nOn 28 February, a woman from [[Amsterdam]] who had visited Lombardy was in home isolation in [[Diemen]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rivm.nl/nieuws/tweede-patient-in-nederland-met-covid-19|title=Tweede pati\u00ebnt in Nederland met COVID-19 {{!}} RIVM|website=www.rivm.nl|access-date=1 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''[[North Macedonia]]''' \u2013\nOn 26 February, North Macedonia confirmed its first case, a woman who tested positive at the Clinic for Infectious Diseases, [[Skopje]]. She had stayed in Italy for a month and had been sick for two weeks. Upon returning to North Macedonia, she immediately reported to the clinic.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://vesti.mk/read/article/https%3A%2F%2Freporter.mk%2Fgjuture%2Fpotvrden-prv-sluchaj-od-koronavirus-vo-makedonija%2F|title=\u041f\u043e\u0442\u0432\u0440\u0434\u0435\u043d \u043f\u0440\u0432 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0458 \u043e\u0434 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 \u0432\u043e \u041c\u0430\u043a\u0435\u0434\u043e\u043d\u0438\u0458\u0430 |trans-title=First confirmed case of coronavirus in Macedonia |date=n.d.|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archiv