lseinstituttet|date=6 March 2020|access-date=7 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''Poland''' \u2013\nOf the country's first five cases, two were from Italy, two were from Germany and one was from the UK.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://polandin.com/47007012/four-new-coronavirus-cases-confirmed-in-poland|title=Four new coronavirus cases confirmed in Poland|first=Telewizja Polska|last=S.A|website=polandin.com|accessdate=8 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''Portugal''' \u2013\nOn 2 March, a doctor who had travelled to Northern Italy and became ill on 29 February was confirmed positive at Hospital de S\u00e3o Jo\u00e3o in [[Porto]]. On 4 March, a 44-year-old man who had travelled to Italy was confirmed positive at the same hospital.\n\n'''Romania''' \u2013\nOn 26 February, Romania confirmed its first case, a man from [[Gorj County|Gorj]] who tested positive after having come in contact with an 71-year-old man from [[Cattolica]], Italy. The Italian man visited his wife's family and had several business meetings in Romania from 18 to 22 February. The Romanian man was admitted to National Institute of Infectious Diseases Prof. Dr. Matei Bal\u0219 in [[Bucharest]].<ref name=\":5\" /><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hotnews.ro/stiri-sanatate-23687251-primul-caz-infectie-coronavirus-confirmat-oficial-romania.htm|title=ULTIMA OR\u0102 LIVEVIDEOTEXT Primul caz de infec\u021bie cu coronavirus, confirmat oficial \u00een Rom\u00e2nia: Un b\u0103rbat din Gorj care a intrat \u00een contact cu italianul care a vizitat recent \u021bara noastr\u0103 \u2013 Sanatate \u2013 HotNews.ro|date=26 February 2020|website=hotnews.ro|language=ro|access-date=26 February 2020}}</ref>\nOn 28 February, a 45-year-old man from [[Maramure\u0219]] who had returned from Italy on 25 February was admitted to the Clinic of Infectious Diseases and then transferred to [[Cluj County|Cluj]].<ref name=\":9\">{{cite web|url=https://www.digi24.ro/stiri/actualitate/doua-noi-posibile-cazuri-de-coronavirus-in-romania-1267704|title=Dou\u0103 noi cazuri de coronavirus confirmate \u00een Rom\u00e2nia|website=digi24.ro|language=ro|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref> A 38-year-old woman who had returned from Bergamo tested positive was admitted to a hospital in [[Timi\u0219oara]].<ref name=\":9\" />\nOn 3 March, a 47-year-old man who had travelled in the same plane with the 38-year-old woman was confirmed positive and admitted to the same hospital.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.digi24.ro/stiri/actualitate/al-patrulea-caz-de-coronavirus-confirmat-in-romania-1269577|title=Al patrulea caz de coronavirus a fost confirmat \u00een Rom\u00e2nia|trans-title=Fourth coronavirus case was confirmed in Romania|language=ro|website=Digi24|date=3 March 2020|access-date=3 March 2020}}</ref>\nThe majority of confirmed cases in Romania are related to Italy.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.digi24.ro/stiri/actualitate/informatii-oficiale-despre-coronavirus-ministerul-de-interne-26-de-persoane-sunt-in-carantina-2077-sunt-monitorizate-la-domiciliu-1266261|title=Coronavirus Rom\u00e2nia, INFORMA\u021aII OFICIALE: 36 de persoane au fost infectate. Primul medic confirmat cu COVID-19|trans-title=Coronavirus Romania, OFFICIAL INFORMATION: 36 people got infected. First medic infected with COVID-19|language=ro|website=Digi24|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|date=11 March 2020|access-date=11 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''Russia''' \u2013\nOn 2 March, a Russian citizen who had returned from Italy was diagnosed.<ref>{{cite news |title=Russian citizen who returned from Italy diagnosed with coronavirus: RIA cites ministry |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-russia/russian-citizen-who-returned-from-italy-diagnosed-with-coronavirus-ria-cites-ministry-idUSKBN20P1JH |accessdate=4 March 2020 |agency=Reuters |date=2 March 2020 }}</ref>\n\n'''San Marino''' \u2013\nOn 27 February, San Marino confirmed its first case, an 88-year-old man with pre-existing medical conditions who was hospitalised at Rimini Hospital.<ref>{{cite 