ciedad/2020/01/31/actualidad/1580509404_469734.html|title=Sanidad confirma en La Gomera el primer caso de coronavirus en Espa\u00f1a|date=1 February 2020|work=El Pa\u00eds|access-date=27 February 2020|language=es|issn=1134-6582}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://en.as.com/en/2020/02/27/football/1582794092_036585.html|title=Valencia fan in Milan last week for UCL tie tests positive for coronavirus|date=27 February 2020|website=AS.com|access-date=27 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last=Bono|first=Ferran|url=https://elpais.com/sociedad/2020/02/27/actualidad/1582795523_075914.html|title=Un periodista que viaj\u00f3 a Mil\u00e1n para cubrir el Valencia-Atalanta, positivo por coronavirus|date=27 February 2020|work=El Pa\u00eds|access-date=27 February 2020|language=es|issn=1134-6582}}</ref><ref name=\":6\">{{cite web|url=https://www.levante-emv.com/comunitat-valenciana/2020/02/27/coronavirus-valencia-nuevos-casos-infectados/1983062.html|title=Sanidad confirma 6 nuevos casos de coronavirus en la C. Valenciana|last=Levante-EMV|website=levante-emv.com|language=es|access-date=27 February 2020}}</ref> A woman who had visited Milan was hospitalised at Hospital de Sagunto, Valencia.<ref name=\":6\" /> An Italian student studying in Valencia who had visited Northern Italy was admitted to Hospital Universitario Doctor Peset.<ref name=\":6\" /> A 22-year-old woman from Tenerife who had travelled to Italy from 19 to 25 February was admitted to Hospital Cl\u00ednic.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.abc.es/espana/catalunya/abci-mujer-22-anos-viajo-italia-tercer-caso-importado-coronavirus-cataluna-202002271249_noticia.html|title=Una tinerfe\u00f1a de 22 a\u00f1os que viaj\u00f3 a Italia, tercer caso \"importado\" de coronavirus en Catalu\u00f1a|date=27 February 2020|website=abc|language=es|access-date=27 February 2020}}</ref> An 18-year-old Italian student studying at IE University, [[Segovia]], who had just returned from Milan, was admitted to Hospital General de Segovia.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.elnortedecastilla.es/segovia/ingresado-joven-habitaciones-20200227182120-nt.html|title=Un alumno italiano de IE University en Segovia, primer caso positivo de coronavirus en la regi\u00f3n|date=27 February 2020|website=El Norte de Castilla|language=es|access-date=27 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.leonoticias.com/castillayleon/primer-coronavirus-castilla-20200227184850-nt.html|title=Confirmados en Segovia y Valladolid los dos primeros casos registrados en Castilla y Le\u00f3n|date=27 February 2020|website=Leonoticias|language=es|access-date=27 February 2020}}</ref>\nOn 28 February, a 27-year-old man from [[Aragon]] with a history of recent trips to Milan tested positive.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.elespanol.com/ciencia/salud/|title=Noticias sobre Salud y Medicina en EL ESPA\u00d1OL|website=El Espa\u00f1ol|language=es-ES|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''Sweden''' \u2013\nOn 26 February, Sweden confirmed that a 30-year-old man who previously visited Northern Italy fell ill three days after returning to Sweden and was admitted to [[Sahlgrenska University Hospital]] in [[Gothenburg]].<ref>{{Cite news|last=Bolin|first=Mattias|url=https://www.svt.se/nyheter/lokalt/vast/bekraftat-coronafall-i-goteborg-person-vardas-pa-sahlgrenska|title=Bekr\u00e4ftat coronafall i G\u00f6teborg \u2013 person v\u00e5rdas p\u00e5 Sahlgrenska|date=26 February 2020|work=SVT Nyheter|access-date=26 February 2020|language=sv}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.expressen.se/gt/en-person-i-goteborg-har-testats-positivt-for-corona/|title=Bekr\u00e4ftat fall av Coronavirus i G\u00f6teborg \u2013 personen har varit i Italien|last=Ekstr\u00f6m|first=reas|website=Expressen|language=sv|access-date=26 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.folkhalsomyndigheten.se/nyheter-och-press/nyhetsarkiv/2020/februari/nytt-bekraftat-fall-av-covid-19/|title=Nytt bekr\u00e4ftat fall av covid-19 \u2013 Folkh\u00e4lsomyndigheten|website=folkhalsomyndigheten.se|language=sv|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref>\nOn 27 February, three patients in their 30s were confirmed positive in [[V\u00e4stra G\u00f6taland County|V\u00e4stra G\u00f6taland]]. Two of them had been in contact with the Gothenburg patient, while the other had previously visited Italy.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.folkhalsomyndigheten.se/nyheter-och-press/nyhetsarkiv/2020/februari/ytterligare-fall-av-covid-19-i-flera-regioner/|title=Ytterligare fall av covid-19 i flera regioner \u2013 Folkh\u00e4lsomyndigheten|website=folkhalsomyndigheten.se|language=sv|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.cision.com/se/vastra-gotalandsregionen/r/tre-nya-bekraftade-fall-av-coronavirusinfektion--covid-19--i-vastra-gotaland,c3048641|title=Tre nya bekr\u00e4ftade fall av coronavirusinfektion (Covid-19) i V\u00e4stra G\u00f6taland|website=News Powered by Cision|language=sv|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref><ref name=\":18\">{{cite web|url=https://www.thelocal.se/20200227/five-new-cases-of-the-coronavirus-in-sweden|title=Sweden confirms five new coronavirus cases, including first patient in Stockholm|last=L\u00f6fgren|first=Emma|date=27 February 2020|website=thelocal.se|publisher=The Local|accessdate=27 February 2020}}</ref>\nOn 28 February, a man in his 50s who had returned from Northern Italy on 24 February tested positive and was admitted to a hospital in [[J\u00f6nk\u00f6ping]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rjl.se/nyheter/nyheter-och-pressmeddelanden/pressmeddelande-28-februari-2020-ytterligare-bekraftat-fall-i-jonkopings-lan-av-nya-coronaviruset-covid-19--45553|title=Pressmeddelande 28 februari 2020: Ytterligare bekr\u00e4ftat fall i J\u00f6nk\u00f6pings l\u00e4n av nya coronaviruset (covid-19), Region J\u00f6nk\u00f6pings l\u00e4n|website=rjl.se|language=sv|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''Switzerland''' \u2013\nOn 25 February, Switzerland confirmed its first case, a 70-year-old man in the canton of [[Canton of Ticino|Ticino]] who had previously visited Milan.<ref name=\"Repubblica_25Feb_Tenerife\" /><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-switzerland-coronavirus-idUSKBN20J1ZO|title=Swiss authorities confirm first case of coronavirus|date=25 February 2020|agency=Reuters|access-date=26 February 2020}}</ref>\nOn 27 February, a 28-year-old IT worker from [[Geneva]] who had recently returned from Milan tested positive and was admitted to [[Geneva University Hospitals|Geneva University Hospital]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bag.admin.ch/bag/en/home/das-bag/aktuell/medienmitteilungen.msg-id-78268.html|title=New coronavirus Covid-19: three new confirmed cases in Switzerland|website=bag.admin.ch|access-date=27 February 2020}}</ref><ref name=\":02\">{{cite web|url=https://www.swissinfo.ch/eng/politics/covid-19_switzerland-confirms-second-coronavirus-case/45582788|title=Switzerland confirms total of four coronavirus cases|last=swissinfo.ch|first=S. W. I.|last2=Corporation|first2=a branch of the Swiss Broadcasting|website=SWI swissinfo.ch|access-date=27 February 2020}}</ref> Two Italian children on vacation in [[Canton of Grisons|Graub\u00fcnden]] tested positive and were hospitalised.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gr.ch/DE/institutionen/verwaltung/djsg/ga/coronavirus/Seiten/Info.aspx|title=Informationen zum Coronavirus|website=gr.ch|access-date=27 February 2020}}</ref><ref name=\":02\" /><ref name=\":92\">{{cite web|url=https://www.bielertagblatt.ch/nachrichten/schweiz/graubuenden-sagt-den-engadiner-skimarathon-ab|title=Graub\u00fcnden sagt den Engadiner Skimarathon ab|website=Bieler Tagblatt|language=de|access-date=27 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227174547/https://www.bielertagblatt.ch/nachrichten/schweiz/graubuenden-sagt-den-engadiner-skimarathon-ab|archive-date=27 February 2020|url-status=dead}}</ref> A 26-year-old man in [[Canton of Aargau|Aargau]] who had visited Verona on a business trip the previous week tested positive and was hospitalised.<ref name=\":02\" /> A 30-year-old woman who visited Milan was admitted to a hospital in [[Z\u00fcrich|Zurich]].<ref name=\":02\" /> A young woman who had travelled to Milan tested positive in [[Canton of Basel-Stadt|Basel-City]]. She worked for a daycare centre in [[Riehen]], and after her test was confirmed, the children at the daycare were put into a two-week quarantine.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-swiss-idUSKCN20L167|title=Swiss coronavirus cases rise to nine as children placed in precautionary quarantine|date=27 February 2020|agency=Reuters|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref> On 28 February, her partner, a 23-year-old man, also tested positive in [[Canton of Basel-Landschaft|Basel-Country]].<ref name=\":21\">{{cite web|url=https://www.rts.ch/info/suisse/11127000-manifestations-d-ampleur-interdites-en-raison-du-coronavirus-conference-de-presse-du-conseil-federal-en-direct.html|title=Les manifestations d'ampleur interdites en Suisse en raison du coronavirus|date=28 February 2020|website=rts.ch|language=fr|access-date=1 March 2020}}</ref> On 29 February, the man's mother tested positive as well. \nOn 28 February, a 45-year-old-man who had travelled to Milan tested positive in [[Z\u00fcrich]].<ref name=\":21\" />\n\n'''Ukraine''' \u2013\nOn 3 March, Ukraine confirmed its first case in [[Chernivtsi]], a man who had travelled from Italy by plane to the Romanian city of [[Suceava]] and then to Ukraine by car with his wife.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/katyagorchinskaya/2020/03/03/first-case-of-coronavirus-registered-in-ukraine/|title=First Case Of Coronavirus Registered in Ukraine|date=3 March 2020|access-date=3 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''United Kingdom''' \u2013\nOn 27 February, the United Kingdom confirmed that a patient who had visited Milan tested positive and was admitted to [[Royal Free Hospital]] in London.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-51656609|title=Two more coronavirus cases confirmed in England|date=27 February 2020|work=BBC News|access-date=27 February 2020}}</ref> Northern Ireland reported its first case, an adult who had travelled from Northern Italy via Dublin and was admitted to Royal Victoria Hospital in [[Belfast]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Kearney|first=Vincent|date=27 February 2020|title=NI coronavirus case had travelled through Dublin|url=https://www.rte.ie/news/health/2020/0227/1117991-ireland-coronavirus/}}</ref>\nOn 28 February, Wales reported its first case, a patient who had returned from northern Italy was treated at a specialist unit in England.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-wales-51450517|title=First case of coronavirus in Wales confirmed|date=28 February 2020|work=BBC News|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Oceania===\n\n'''Australia''' \u2013\nAt least one case has travel history to Italy.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.health.gov.au/news/health-alerts/novel-coronavirus-2019-ncov-health-alert|title=Coronavirus (COVID-19) health alert|first=Australian Government Department of|last=Health|date=6 February 2020|website=Australian Government Department of Health|accessdate=8 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''New Zealand''' \u2013\nOn 4 March, the New Zealand Ministry of Health confirmed its second case, a woman in her 30s who returned to [[Auckland]] from Northern Italy.<ref>{{cite news |title=Second Case of COVID-19 Confirmed in NZ |url=https://www.health.govt.nz/news-media/media-releases/second-case-covid-19-confirmed-nz |accessdate=4 March 2020 |work=Ministry of Health NZ }}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n{{Portal bar|COVID-19|Italy|Current events|Medicine|Viruses}}\n* [[:Template:2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic articles]]<!-- Template will not display if transcluded, since it causes the page to exceed the Post-expand include size -->\n* [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in San Marino]]\n* [[Timeline of the 2019\u20132020 coronavirus pandemic in March 2020]]\n* [[2020 coronavirus pandemic on cruise ships]]\n* [[Pandemic]]\n* [[Epidemiology of COVID-19]]\n* [[2009 flu pandemic in Europe]]\n* [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Europe]]\n* [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in France]]\n* [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Germany]]\n* [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Malta]]\n* [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Spain]]\n* [[List of epidemics]]\n* [[Coronavirus disease 2019]]\n* [[Coronavirus disease]]s, a group of closely related syndromes\n* [[Severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2]]\n* [[Severe acute respiratory syndrome-related coronavirus]]\n* [[Contact tracing]], inquiry opened immediately to identify and contact everyone who has been in close contact with an infected person and subsequent collection of further information about these contacts\n\n==References==\n<references /><!-- Do not replace with {{reflist}}, since that would hide references if the Post-expand include size of the page is exceeded -->\n\n==External links==\n* {{cite web |url = http://www.salute.gov.it/nuovocoronavirus |publisher=[[Ministry of Health (Italy)|Ministero della Salute]] |title=Official website|language=italian}}\n* {{cite web | url = http://opendatadpc.maps.arcgis.com/apps/opsdashboard/index.html#/b0c68bce2cce478eaac82fe38d4138b1 | title = Geomap and open data on the diffusion of COVID-19 in Italy | website = [[Protezione Civile]] | archive-url = http://archive.is/wip/fViDD | archive-date = 12 March 2020 | url-status = live}} (desktop version)\n* {{cite web |url=https://coronavirus-global.com/italy |title=Coronavirus Italy updates and news |trans-title=Latest news and statistics of coronavirus in Italy. |access-date=4 April 2020 |language=English, French, Spanish, Portuguese, German, Italian, Swedish, Norwegian, Finnish, Estonian, Russian}}\n* [http://italy.coronamapper.com Map of the virus in Italy]\n* {{cite web |publisher=[[Il Sole 24 Ore]]|title=Coronavirus in Italia |url =https://lab24.ilsole24ore.com/coronavirus/|language=italian}}\n* {{cite web |first=Emanuele|las