ases = \n| total_ili       = \n| website         = {{URL|www.salute.gov.it/nuovocoronavirus}}\n}}\n\nAn ongoing [[2019\u20132020 coronavirus pandemic|worldwide pandemic]] of [[coronavirus disease 2019]] ({{nowrap|COVID-19}}), a novel infectious disease caused by [[severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus&nbsp;2]] ({{nowrap|SARS-CoV-2}}), was first confirmed to have spread to Italy on 31 January 2020, when two Chinese tourists in Rome tested positive for the virus.<ref name=\"Corriere_20Jan\">{{cite web |title=Coronavirus: Primi due casi in Italia|url=https://www.corriere.it/cronache/20_gennaio_30/coronavirus-italia-corona-9d6dc436-4343-11ea-bdc8-faf1f56f19b7.shtml |website=Corriere della sera |accessdate=31 January 2020 |date=31 January 2020|language=it}}</ref> One week later an Italian man repatriated back to Italy from the city of [[Wuhan]], China, was hospitalised and confirmed as the third case in Italy.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-italy-idUSKBN20F0UI|title=First Italian dies of coronavirus as outbreak flares in north|date=21 February 2020|agency=Reuters|access-date=6 March 2020}}</ref> A cluster of cases was later detected, starting with 16 confirmed cases in [[Lombardy]] on 21 February,<ref name=\"ThomReut_IT_16cluster_21Feb\">{{cite news | last1= Anzolin | first1= Elisa | last2= Amante | first2= Angelo | title= Coronavirus outbreak grows in northern Italy, 16 cases reported in one day | date=21 February 2020 | agency=[[Thomson Reuters]] | url= https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-italy/coronavirus-outbreak-grows-in-northern-italy-16-cases-reported-in-one-day-idUSKBN20F0UI |accessdate=21 February 2020 |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20200221225322/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-italy/coronavirus-outbreak-grows-in-northern-italy-16-cases-reported-in-one-day-idUSKBN20F0UI |archivedate= 21 February 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref> and 60 additional cases and the first deaths on 22 February.<ref name=\"CorrieredSera_76_recent_cases\" /> By the beginning of March, the virus had spread to all regions of Italy.<ref>{{cite news |title=Coronavirus. Colpite tutte le regioni. La Protezione civile: ecco i numeri aggiornati |url=https://www.avvenire.it/attualita/pagine/coronavirus-aggiornamento-5-marzo-2020 |accessdate=19 March 2020 |work=Avvenire |date=5 March 2020 |language=it}}</ref>\n\nOn 31 January, the Italian government suspended all flights to and from China and declared a state of emergency. In February, eleven municipalities in [[northern Italy]] were identified as the centres of the two main Italian clusters and placed under quarantine. The majority of positive cases in other regions traced back to these two clusters.<ref name=\":8\">{{cite web|url=https://www.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/22/news/coronavirus_in_italia_aggiornamento_ora_per_ora-249241616/|title=Coronavirus in Italia: aggiornamento ora per ora|date=22 February 2020|website=la Repubblica|language=it|access-date=27 February 2020}}</ref> On 8 March 2020, Prime Minister [[Giuseppe Conte]] expanded the quarantine to all of Lombardy and 14 other northern provinces, and on the following day to all of Italy, [[2020 Italy coronavirus lockdown|placing more than 60 million people in quarantine]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Coronavirus: Northern Italy quarantines 16 million people |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-51787238 |website=BBC |accessdate=8 March 2020 |date=8 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"auto\">{{cite news |title=All of Italy to be placed on coronavirus lockdown |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-51810673 |accessdate=9 March 2020 |work=BBC News |date=9 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.sky.com/story/coronavirus-italy-sees-largest-daily-rise-in-deaths-and-confirmed-cases-11953192|title=Coronavirus: Italy deaths jump to 463, with 300 in just one region|publisher=Sky News|accessdate=10 March 2020}}</ref> On 11 March 2020, Conte prohibited nearly all commercial activity except for supermarkets and pharmacies.<ref name=\":12\">{{cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/europe/merkel-coronavirus-germany/2020/03/11/e276252a-6399-11ea-8a8e-5c5336b32760_story.html|title=Italy ramps up coronavirus lockdown, Merkel warns virus could infect two-thirds of Germany|last=Harlan|first=Chico|last2=Morris|first2=Loveday|website=The Washington Post|access-date=12 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\":13\">{{Cite news|last=Rome|first=Eric Sylvers in Milan and Giovanni Legorano in|url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/italy-hardens-nationwide-quarantine-11583962093|title=Italy Hardens Nationwide Quarantine|date=12 March 2020|work=The Wall Street Journal|access-date=12 March 2020|issn=0099-9660}}</ref> On 21 March, the Italian government closed all non-essential businesses and industries, with additional restrictions to movement of people.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Safi |first1=Michael |last2=Giuffrida |first2=Angela |last3=Farrer |first3=Martin |title=Coronavirus: Italy bans any movement inside country as toll nears 5,500 |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/22/italian-pm-warns-of-worst-crisis-since-ww2-as-coronavirus-deaths-leap-by-almost-800 |accessdate=22 March 2020 |work=The Guardian |date=22 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 6 March 2020, the Italian College of Anesthesia, Analgesia, Resuscitation and Intensive Care (SIAARTI) published [[medical ethics]] recommendations regarding [[triage]] protocols that might be employed.<ref>{{cite techreport|url=http://www.siaarti.it/SiteAssets/News/COVID19%20-%20documenti%20SIAARTI/SIAARTI%20-%20Covid19%20-%20Raccomandazioni%20di%20etica%20clinica.pdf|title=Raccomandazioni di etica clinica per l\u2019ammissione a trattamenti intensivi e per la loro sospensione, in condizioni eccezionali di squilibrio tra necessit\u00e0 e risorse disponibili|institution=Italian College of Anesthesia, Analgesia, Resuscitation and Intensive Care (SIAARTI)|language=it|date=6 March 2020|access-date=12 March 2020|url-status=live|format=PDF|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200312202813/http://www.siaarti.it/SiteAssets/News/COVID19%20-%20documenti%20SIAARTI/SIAARTI%20-%20Covid19%20-%20Raccomandazioni%20di%20etica%20clinica.pdf|archive-date=12 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theatlantic.com/ideas/archive/2020/03/who-gets-hospital-bed/607807/|title=The Extraordinary Decisions Facing Italian Doctors|last=Mounk|first=Yascha|date=11 March 2020|work=[[The Atlantic]]|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200312233745/https://www.theatlantic.com/ideas/archive/2020/03/who-gets-hospital-bed/607807/|archive-date=12 March 2020|access-date=12 March 2020|quote=Now the Italian College of Anesthesia, Analgesia, Resuscitation and Intensive Care (SIAARTI) has published guidelines for the criteria that doctors and nurses should follow in these extraordinary circumstances. The document begins by likening the moral choices facing Italian doctors to the forms of wartime triage that are required in the field of \"catastrophe medicine.\"}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.politico.eu/article/coronavirus-italy-doctors-tough-calls-survival/|title=Italian doctors on coronavirus frontline face tough calls on whom to save|last=Privitera|first=Greta|date=11 March 2020|work=[[Politico]]|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200312125640/https://www.politico.eu/article/coronavirus-italy-doctors-tough-calls-survival/|archive-date=12 March 2020|access-date=12 March 2020|quote=\u2026the Italian Society of Anesthesia, Analgesia, Resuscitation and Intensive Care, who co-authored new guidelines on how to prioritize treatment of coronavirus cases in hospitals\u2026}}</ref>\n\n{{As of|2020|04|11}}, Italy is one of the world's centres of active coronavirus cases with 100,269 active cases.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://gisanddata.maps.arcgis.com/apps/opsdashboard/index.html#/bda7594740fd40299423467b48e9ecf6|title=Coronavirus COVID-19 Global Cases by the Center for Systems Science and Engineering (CSSE) at Johns Hopkins |access-date=25 March 2020}}</ref> The total of confirmed cases is 152,271, with 19,468 deaths, and 32,534 recoveries or dismissals.<ref name=\"Min_Salute_Situazione\">{{cite web|url=http://www.salute.gov.it/portale/nuovocoronavirus/dettaglioContenutiNuovoCoronavirus.jsp?lingua=italiano&id=5351&area=nuovoCoronavirus&menu=vuoto|title=Covid-19 \u2013 Situazione in Italia|website=salute.gov.it|publisher=Ministero della Salute|language=it|accessdate=13 March 2020}}</ref> By 11 April, Italy had conducted about 963,500 tests for the virus.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.salute.gov.it/imgs/C_17_pagineAree_5351_26_file.pdf|title=AGGIORNAMENTO 21/03/2020 ORE 17.00|date=21 March 2020|url-status=live|access-date=19 March 2020}}</ref> Due to the finite number of tests performed, the real number of infected people in Italy, as in other countries, is estimated to be higher than the official count.<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Flaxman |first1=Seth |last2=Swapnil |first2=Mishra |last3=Gandy |first3=Axel |display-authors=etal |title=Report 13: Estimating the number of infections and the impact of non-pharmaceutical interventions on COVID-19 in 11 European countries |date=30 March 2020 |pages=1\u201335 |doi=10.25561/77731 |url=https://spiral.imperial.ac.uk:8443/handle/10044/1/77731 |accessdate=31 March 2020 |publisher=Imperial College London}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal |last=Lau |first=Hien |last2=Khosrawipour |first2=Veria |last3=Kocbach |first3=Piotr |last4=Mikolajczyk |first4=Agata |last5=Ichii |first5=Hirohito |last6=Schubert |first6=Justyna |last7=Bania |first7=Jacek |last8=Khosrawipour |first8=Tanja |date=14 March 2020 |title=Internationally lost COVID-19 cases |url=http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S1684118220300736 |journal=Journal of Microbiology, Immunology and Infection  |doi=10.1016/j.jmii.2020.03.013 |pmid=32205091 |pmc=7102572 |issn=1684-1182}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=The total number of Italian coronavirus cases could be '10 times higher' than known tally, according to one official |url=https://www.cnbc.com/2020/03/24/italian-coronavirus-cases-seen-10-times-higher-than-official-tally.html |accessdate=31 March 2020 |publisher=CNBC |date=24 March 2020 }}</ref> On 19 March, Italy became the country with the highest number of confirmed coronavirus deaths in the world, but on 11 April it was overcome by the United States.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/world/2020/03/19/coronavirus-italy-now-has-more-covid-19-deaths-than-china/2873835001/|title=Grim milestone: Italy's coronavirus deaths surpass China's|first=Eric J. Lyman and Kim|last=Hjelmgaard|website=USA Today}}</ref>\n\n==Background==\nOn 31 December 2019, the Health Commission of [[Wuhan]], Hubei, China, informed the [[World Health Organization|WHO]] about a cluster of acute pneumonia cases with unknown origin in its province. On 9 January 2020, the [[Chinese Center for Disease Control and Prevention]] (CCDC) reported the identification of a [[novel coronavirus]] (later identified as the [[SARS-CoV-2]]) as the cause.<ref>{{cite web |title=Covid-19 \u2013 Situazione nel mondo |url=http://www.salute.gov.it/portale/nuovocoronavirus/dettaglioContenutiNuovoCoronavirus.jsp?lingua=italiano&id=5338&area=nuovoCoronavirus&menu=vuoto |website=salute.gov.it |accessdate=4 March 2020 |language=IT}}</ref> In late January 2020, following the [[Mainland China during the 2019\u20132020 coronavirus outbreak|developments of COVID-19 outbreak in mainland China]], on 3 February, Italy set up enhanced screening measures, including thermal cameras and medical staff at airports.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n==Timeline==\n{{Update section |date=March 2020}}\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic data/Italy medical cases chart}}\n\n===First confirmed cases===\nOn 31 January, the first two cases of COVID-19 were confirmed in Rome. A Chinese couple, originally from Wuhan, who had arrived in Italy on 23 January via [[Milan Malpensa Airport]], travelled from the airport to [[Verona]], then to Parma, arriving in Rome on 28 January. The next afternoon, they developed a cough, and by evening the man had a fever; the couple were taken to the [[Lazzaro Spallanzani National Institute for Infectious Diseases]] where they tested positive for SARS-CoV-2 and were hospitalised.<ref name=\"prima\">{{cite web|url=https://www.corriere.it/cronache/20_gennaio_31/virus-primi-due-casi-italia-due-cinesi-marito-moglie-italia-dieci-giorni-e365df1c-43b3-11ea-bdc8-faf1f56f19b7.shtml|title=Prima a Milano, poi l'hotel a Roma: le tappe dei 7 giorni di viaggio della coppia contagiata|last=Frignani|first=Rinaldo|date=31 January 2020|website=Corriere della Sera|language=it|access-date=7 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Corriere_20Jan\"/> On 2 February, a team from the same institute composed of scientists [[Maria Rosaria Capobianchi]], [[Francesca Colavita]], and Concetta Castilletti isolated the genomic sequence of the virus and uploaded it to [[GenBank]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Armstrong |first1=Mark |title=Italian scientists isolate DNA sequence of coronavirus |url=https://www.euronews.com/2020/02/02/italian-scientists-isolate-dna-sequence-of-coronavirus |accessdate=5 April 2020 |work=euronews |date=2 February 2020 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://tg24.sky.it/cronaca/photogallery/2020/02/02/coronavirus-italia-spallanzani-roma.html |work=[[Sky TG24]]|accessdate=2 February 2020|language=italian|title=Le tre ricercatrici che hanno isolato il Coronavirus allo Spallanzani di Roma.}}</ref>\n\nOn 31 January, the Italian government suspended all flights to and from China and declared a state of emergency with the duration of six months. Prime Minister [[Giuseppe Conte]] said Italy was the first EU country to take this kind of precautionary measure.<ref name=\"thelocal-flight\">{{cite web|url=https://www.thelocal.it/20200131/italy-suspends-all-china-flights-after-coronavirus-cases-confirmed-in-rome/|title=Italy suspends all China flights as coronavirus cases confirmed in Rome|date=31 January 2020|website=THELOCAL|access-date=26 February 2020}}</ref> The government also introduced thermal scanners and temperature checks on international passengers arriving at Italian airports.<ref name=\":0\">{{cite web|url=https://www.corriere.it/cronache/20_febbraio_04/coronavirus-controlli-gli-scanner-termici-aeroporti-italiani-c10b73d2-4796-11ea-bec1-6ac729c309c6.shtml|title=Coronavirus, controlli con gli scanner termici negli aeroporti italiani|last=Berberi|first=Leonard|date=2 April 2020|website=Corriere della Sera|language=it|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 6 February, an Italian repatriated from Wuhan tested positive for COVID-19, bringing the total number of cases in Italy to three.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.cnn.com/asia/live-news/coronavirus-outbreak-02-06-20-intl-hnk/index.html|title=February 6 coronavirus news|first1=Jessie |last1=Yeung |first2=Adam |last2=Renton |first3=Steve|last3=George|date=6 February 2020|publisher=CNN}}</ref>\n\nOn 22 February, the repatriated Italian recovered and was discharged from the hospital.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.open.online/2020/02/22/coronavirus-bollettino-dello-spallanzani-guarito-il-ricercatore-italiano-verra-dimesso-oggi/|title=Coronavirus, bollettino dello Spallanzani: guarito il ricercatore italiano, verr\u00e0 dimesso oggi. Niccol\u00f2 \"sta benissimo\" \u2013 Il video|date=22 February 2020|website=Open|language=it-IT|access-date=23 February 2020}}</ref> On 22 and 26 February, the two previously infected Chinese tourists tested negative for COVID-19 at Lazzaro Spallanzani National Institute in Rome.<ref name=\":2\">{{cite web|url=https://www.ilmessaggero.it/mondo/coronavirus_diretta_morti_contagi_oggi_ultime_notizie_26_febbraio_2020-5075865.html|title=Coronavirus, diretta. Contagi a quota 424, primo caso in Puglia, 12 morti. Lombardia, Fontana \u00e8 negativo, ma resta in isolamento per 14 giorni|website=Il Messaggero}}</ref>\n\n===Clusters in northern Italy===\n====Lombardy====\nThe [[Lombardy]] outbreak came to light when a 38-year-old Italian tested positive in [[Codogno]], a [[comune]] in the [[province of Lodi]]. On 14 February, he felt unwell and went to a doctor in [[Castiglione d'Adda]]. He was prescribed treatments for influenza.<ref name=\"Repubblica_Codogno_doctors\" /> On 16 February, as the man's condition worsened, he went to Codogno Hospital, reporting respiratory problems.<ref name=\"Repubblica_Codogno_doctors\">{{Cite news |title=Codogno, i medici dell'ospedale in trincea: \"Quelle accuse del premier fanno pi\u00f9 male della malattia\"|language=Italian |work=la Repubblica |date=26 February 2020 |url= https://www.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/26/news/codogno_i_medici_dell_ospedale_in_trincea_quelle_accuse_del_premier_fanno_piu_male_della_malattia_-249593374/ |accessdate=26 February 2020}}</ref> Initially there was no suspicion of COVID-19, so no additional precautionary measures were taken, and the virus was able to infect other patients and health workers.<ref name=\"urlMailand:NZZ\">{{cite web |url=https://www.nzz.ch/international/mailand-coronavirus-epidemie-begann-in-spital-ld.1542330 |title=Mailand: Coronavirus-Epidemie begann in Spital |accessdate=24 February 2020 |website= nzz.ch (Neue Zurcher Zeitung)}}</ref> On 19 February, the wife of the patient revealed he had met an Italian friend who had returned from China on 21 January, who subsequently tested negative.<ref name=\"Repubblica_Codogno_doctors\" /> Later, the patient, his pregnant wife and a friend tested positive.<ref name=\"Repubblica_Codogno_doctors\" /> On 20 February, three more cases were confirmed after the patients reported symptoms of [[pneumonia]].<ref name=\":1\">{{cite news |title=Coronavirus, primi tre contagi in Italia: 38enne, sua moglie e un amico in terapia intensiva. La donna insegna in un liceo |language=Italian |publisher=La Repubblica |url= https://milano.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/21/news/coronavirus_a_milano_contaggiato_38enne_e_un_italiano_ricoverato_a_codogno-249121707/?ref=RHPPTP-BH-I249146878-C12-P1-S1.12-T1 |accessdate=21 February 2020 |date=21 February 2020}}</ref> Thereafter, extensive screenings and checks were performed on everyone that had possibly been in contact with or near the infected subjects.<ref name=\"Messaggero_22Feb\">{{cite news |url= https://www.ilmessaggero.it/italia/coronavirus_diretta_lombardia_codogno_italiano_ultime_notizie-5064423.html |title=Coronavirus, diretta: morto uomo di 78 anni a Padova, \u00e8 la prima vittima italiana |website=Il Messaggero |date=22 February 2020 |accessdate=22 February 2020 |language=Italian}}</ref> It has been subsequently reported that the origin of these cases has a possible connection to the first European local transmission that occurred in [[Munich]], Germany, on 19 January 2020, consistent with phylogenetic analysis of viral genome.<ref name=\"Repubblica_Munich_Codogno\">{{cite news |last1=Luna |first1=Riccardo |title=Coronavirus: il paziente tedesco |url=https://rep.repubblica.it/pwa/generale/2020/03/05/news/coronavirus-250377117/ |accessdate=11 March 2020 |work=La Repubblica |date=5 March 2020 |language=it}}</ref><ref name=\"nextstrain\">{{cite web|url=https://nextstrain.org/ncov?dmax=2020-03-08&dmin=2019-12-15&fbclid=IwAR3UreH6NMoS8IjQqWOJpYdTX_Ygc5bW4gcBBf2gWe_QTDwxIL0oLMuwSgY|title=Genomic epidemiology of novel coronavirus (hCoV-19)| website=nextstrain.org|accessdate=10 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=pmid32003551>{{cite journal |last1=Rothe |first1=Camilla |last2=Schunk |first2=Mirjam |last3=Sothmann |first3=Peter |last4=Bretzel |first4=Gisela |last5=Froeschl |first5=Guenter |last6=Wallrauch |first6=Claudia |last7=Zimmer |first7=Thorbj\u00f6rn |last8=Thiel |first8=Verena |last9=Janke |first9=Christian |last10=Guggemos |first10=Wolfgang |last11=Seilmaier |first11=Michael |last12=Drosten |first12=Christian  |author-link12=Christian Drosten |last13=Vollmar |first13=Patrick |last14=Zwirglmaier |first14=Katrin |last15=Zange |first15=Sabine |last16=W\u00f6lfel |first16=Roman |last17=Hoelscher |first17=Michael |title=Transmission of 2019-nCoV Infection from an Asymptomatic Contact in Germany |journal=New England Journal of Medicine |date=5 March 2020 |volume=382 |issue=10 |pages=970\u2013971 |doi=10.1056/NEJMc2001468 |pmid=32003551 |pmc=7120970 }}</ref> The 38-year-old man was asymptomatic for weeks, reportedly led an active social life and potentially interacted with dozens of people before spreading the virus at Codogno Hospital.<ref name=\"Repubblica_Codogno_doctors\" /><ref name=\"urlMailand:NZZ\" /> Afterward, he was transferred to [[Policlinico San Matteo]] in [[Pavia]],<ref>{{Cite news |url= https://www.liberoquotidiano.it/news/italia/13566825/coronavirus-paziente-uno-codogno-trasferimento-pavia.html |title=Coronavirus, il 38enne paziente uno di Codogno trasferito nella notte a Pavia |website=liberoquotidiano.it |accessdate=25 February 2020}}</ref> and his wife to [[Ospedale Luigi Sacco|Sacco Hospital]] in Milan.<ref>{{Cite news |url= https://edition.cnn.com/asia/live-news/coronavirus-outbreak-02-25-20-hnk-intl/h_485832164169510b66e7bb07479c75b0 |title=Italian authorities identify first known patient to have caught coronavirus in Lombardy |first1=Helen |last1=Regan |first2=Adam |last2=Renton |date=25 February 2020 |publisher=CNN |accessdate=25 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url= https://milano.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/25/news/coronavirus_paziente_1_ancora_grave_ma_stazionario_la_moglie_incinta_sta_bene-249550115/ |title=Coronavirus, \"paziente 1\" ancora grave ma stazionario, la moglie incinta sta bene |language=Italian |date=25 February 2020 |work=la Repubblica |accessdate=25 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Emergenza coronavirus (49496308758).jpg|thumb|upright=1.13|[[Protezione Civile|Civil Protection]] volunteers carrying out health checks at [[Guglielmo Marconi Airport]]]]\nOn 21 February 16 more cases were confirmed \u2013 14 in Lombardy, including the doctor who prescribed treatments to the 38-year-old Codogno man,<ref name=\"Repubblica_Codogno_doctors\" /> and two in [[Veneto]]. On 22 February, a 77-year-old woman from [[Casalpusterlengo]], who suffered from pneumonia and visited the same emergency room as the 38-year-old from Codogno, died in Lombardy.<ref>{{Cite news |url= https://www.tgcom24.mediaset.it/cronaca/lombardia/coronavirus-morta-una-donna-in-lombardia-seconda-vittima-italiana_15150431-202002a.shtml|title=Coronavirus, morta una donna in Lombardia: seconda vittima italiana |website=Tgcom24 |language=Italian |accessdate=22 February 2020}}</ref> Including the 78-year-old man who died in Veneto, the number of cases in Italy rose to 79.<ref name=\"CorrieredSera_76_recent_cases\" /><ref>{{Cite news |title=Coronavirus, in Veneto la prima vittima, Adriano Trevisan, 78 anni. Venti contagiati in Italia. Conte: \"Nuove misure\" |date=22 February 2020 |work=la Repubblica |url= https://www.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/22/news/cina_coronavirus_italia_virus_wuhan_influenza_codogno_lombardia_veneto_adriano_trevisan-249215365/}}</ref> Of the 76 newly discovered cases, 54 were found in Lombardy, including one patient in [[San Raffaele Hospital]] in Milan<ref>{{Cite news |url= https://www.corriere.it/cronache/20_febbraio_22/coronavirus-italia-nuovi-contagi-lombardia-veneto-245e72d4-5540-11ea-8418-2150c9ca483e.shtml |title=Coronavirus, due casi a Milano |first=Simona |last=Ravizza |date=22 February 2020 |website=Corriere della Sera |language=Italian |accessdate=23 February 2020}}</ref> and eight patients in [[Policlinico San Matteo]] in [[Pavia]],<ref>{{Cite news |title=Coronavirus, a Pavia 8 pazienti ricoverati al San Matteo: anche una coppia di medici |language=Italian |website=Il Messaggero |date=22 February 2020 |url= https://www.ilmessaggero.it/italia/coronavirus_pavia_medici_contagiati_pieve_porto_morone_chignolo_po_cosa_sta_succedendo_22_febbraio_2020-5068178.html |accessdate=23 February 2020}}</ref> 17 in Veneto, two in [[Emilia-Romagna]], two in [[Lazio]] and one in [[Piedmont]].<ref>{{Cite news |first=Simona |last=Ravizza |title=Coronavirus, due casi a Milano |date=22 February 2020 |language=Italian |website=Corriere della Sera |url= https://www.corriere.it/cronache/20_febbraio_22/coronavirus-italia-nuovi-contagi-lombardia-veneto-245e72d4-5540-11ea-8418-2150c9ca483e.shtml |accessdate=22 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 23 February, a 68-year-old woman with cancer from [[Trescore Cremasco]] died in [[Crema, Lombardy|Crema]]. The number of cases in Italy rose to 152, including fourteen patients being treated at Policlinico San Matteo in Pavia.<ref>{{Cite news |url= https://www.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/23/news/coronavirus_italia-249329434/ |title=Coronavirus, terza vittima in Italia: \u00e8 una donna ricoverata a Crema. 152 casi positivi |date=23 February 2020 |website=la Repubblica |language=Italian |access-date=23 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.globalist.it/news/2020/02/23/coronavirus-sale-a-14-il-numero-dei-casi-ricoverati-a-pavia-2053548.html |title=Coronavirus, sale a 14 il numero dei casi ricoverati a Pavia |publisher=globalist.it |language=Italian |accessdate=24 February 2020}}</ref> On 24 February, an 84-year-old man with pre-existing medical conditions from [[Villa di Serio]] died in [[Bergamo]] while hospitalised in the Papa Giovanni XXIII Hospital.<ref>{{Cite news |url= https://www.huffingtonpost.it/entry/quarto-morto-in-italia-per-il-coronavirus-aveva-84-anni_it_5e5381b7c5b6b82aa65555f4 |title=Quarto morto in Italia per il coronavirus, aveva 84 anni |date=24 February 2020 |website=L'HuffPost |language=Italian |accessdate=24 February 2020}}</ref> An 88-year-old man from [[Caselle Landi]], who resided in Codogno, died on the same day.<ref>{{Cite news |url= https://www.tgcom24.mediaset.it/cronaca/coronavirus-quarta-vittima-a-bergamo-in-lombardia-scoperti-150-casi_15242453-202002a.shtml |title=Coronavirus, in Italia si contano sei vittime e 230 contagi &#124; In Lombardia il numero maggiore dei casi |website=Tgcom24}}</ref><ref name=\"Repubblica_24Jan\" /> An 80-year-old man from [[Castiglione d\u2019Adda]] died at the Luigi Sacco Hospital in Milan. He was previously hospitalised in Lodi because of a heart attack, and then transferred to Milan when confirmed as positive.<ref name=\"Repubblica_24Jan\">{{Cite news |title=Coronavirus, sei morti in Italia, 229 contagi. Le vittime di oggi hanno tutte pi\u00f9 di 80 anni |language=Italian |website=la Repubblica |date=24 February 2020 |url= https://www.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/24/news/coronavirus_149_i_casi_confermati_conte_i_contagi_possono_crescere_-249427098/ |accessdate=24 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.ansa.it/canale_saluteebenessere/notizie/sanita/2020/02/24/coronavirus-_60aae600-8535-44d9-86de-48c4b71478ef.html |title=Coronavirus: sesta vittima in Italia, morto 80enne a Milano. Smentita dalla Regione Lombardia la morte della donna a Brescia \u2013 Salute & Benessere |date=22 February 2020 |website=ANSA.it}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url= https://www.corriere.it/cronache/20_febbraio_24/coronavirus-chi-sono-vittime-italia-74e27360-56f6-11ea-b89d-a5ca249e9e1e.shtml |title=L'ex muratore , gli anziani ricoverati: chi sono le vittime |last=Del Frate |first=Claudio |date=24 February 2020 |website=Corriere della Sera |language=Italian |accessdate=24 February 2020}}</ref> A 62-year-old man with pre-existing medical conditions from Castiglione d'Adda died in [[Ospedale Sant'Anna|Sant'Anna Hospital]] in [[Como]].<ref>{{cite web |location=Italy |url= https://www.fanpage.it/attualita/corona-la-settima-vittima-e-un-62enne-di-castiglione-dadda-era-ricoverato-allospedale-di-como/ |title=Coronavirus, c'\u00e8 la settima vittima italiana: un 62enne di Castiglione d'Adda, era ricoverato a Como |website=Fanpage}}</ref> Lombardy governor [[Attilio Fontana]] announced that the number of cases in Lombardy had risen to 172, with a total of 229 confirmed in Italy.<ref name=\"Corriere_24Feb\">{{cite web|url=https://www.corriere.it/cronache/20_febbraio_24/coronavirus-italia-ultime-notizie-oggi-nord-23035e06-56ce-11ea-b89d-a5ca249e9e1e.shtml|title=Coronavirus in Italia, i contagi sono pi\u00f9 di 200: gli ultimi aggiornamenti|last=Online|first=Chiara Severgnini e Redazione|date=24 February 2020|website=Corriere della Sera|language=it|access-date=24 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |title=Coronavirus, quarto morto, \u00e8 un 84enne di Bergamo. |language=Italian |work=la Repubblica |date=24 February 2020 |url= https://www.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/24/news/coronavirus_149_i_casi_confermati_conte_i_contagi_possono_crescere_-249427098/ |accessdate=24 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |title=Coronavirus, sette morti in Italia, 229 contagi |language=Italian |work=la Repubblica |date=24 February 2020 |url= https://www.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/24/news/coronavirus_149_i_casi_confermati_conte_i_contagi_possono_crescere_-249427098/ |accessdate=25 February 2020}}</ref> On 25 February, an 84-year-old man from [[Nembro]], a 91-year-old man from [[San Fiorano]] and an 83-year-old woman from Codogno died from complications caused by the infections.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Del Frate |first=Claudio |title=L'ex muratore , gli anziani ricoverati: chi sono le vittime |language=Italian |work=Corriere della Sera |date=24 February 2020 |url= https://www.corriere.it/cronache/20_febbraio_24/coronavirus-chi-sono-vittime-italia-74e27360-56f6-11ea-b89d-a5ca249e9e1e.shtml |accessdate=25 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |title=Coronavirus in Lombardia, salgono a 206 le persone contagiate |language=Italian |work=la Repubblica |date=25 February 2020 |url= https://milano.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/25/news/coronavirus_in_lombardia_salgono_a_206_le_persone_contagiate-249527654/ |accessdate=25 February 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Repubblica_25Feb_count\">{{Cite news |url= https://www.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/25/news/coronavirus_toscana-249520102/ |title=Coronavirus, 325 casi in Italia. Altri tre morti in Lombardia e uno in Veneto, le vittime diventano 11 |date=25 February 2020 |work=la Repubblica |language=Italian |access-date=25 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe number of cases in Emilia-Romagna rose to 23, spreading through the provinces of [[Province of Piacenza|Piacenza]], [[Province of Parma|Parma]], [[Province of Modena|Modena]] and [[Province of Rimini|Rimini]]. These were all linked to the Lombardy cluster.<ref>{{Cite news |url= https://parma.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/24/news/coronavirus_primi_due_casi_in_provincia_di_parma-249436934/ |title=Coronavirus, primi due casi in provincia di Parma|date=24 February 2020 |website=la Repubblica |language=Italian |accessdate=26 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.ilrestodelcarlino.it/cronaca/coronavirus-oggi-1.5043974 |title=Coronavirus oggi Emilia Romagna: 19 contagiati, uno \u00e8 a Modena. Numero verde 800033033 |first=il Resto del |last=Carlino |date=24 February 2020 |work=il Resto del Carlino}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url= https://bologna.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/25/news/coronavirus_23_contagiati_in_emilia_romagna-249540542/ |title=Coronavirus: 23 contagiati in Emilia Romagna. Accertamenti su un riminese tornato dall'estero |date=25 February 2020 |website=la Repubblica |language=Italian |accessdate=25 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |title=Coronavirus, salgono a quattro i casi positivi nel territorio di Parma |language=Italian |work=la Repubblica |date=25 February 2020 |url= https://parma.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/25/news/coronavirus_parma_altri_due_casi_a-249527788/ |accessdate=26 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |title=Coronavirus, caso positivo a Bardi. Il sindaco: \"Non ci sono criticit\u00e0\" |language=Italian |work=la Repubblica |date=26 February 2020 |url= https://parma.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/26/news/coronavirus_caso_positivo_a_bardi_il_sindaco_non_esiste_al_momento_nessuna_criticita_-249613641/ |accessdate=26 February 2020}}</ref> A new case linked to the outbreak in Lombardy appeared in [[Palermo]], Sicily, when a 60-year-old woman from Bergamo tested positive and was admitted to Cervello Hospital.<ref>{{Cite news |url= https://www.corriere.it/cronache/20_febbraio_25/coronavirus-turista-bergamasca-positiva-palermo-isolata-comitiva-d492dee2-57a7-11ea-a2d7-f1bec9902bd3.shtml |title=Coronavirus, turista bergamasca positiva a Palermo. Isolata la comitiva |first=Salvo |last=Toscano |date=25 February 2020 |work=Corriere della Sera}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url= https://palermo.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/25/news/palermo_caso_sospetto_a_palermo_turista_di_bergamo_ricoverata_al_cervello-249516268/ |title=Il coronavirus arriva a Palermo: turista di Bergamo positiva ai primi test |date=25 February 2020 |work=la Repubblica |language=Italian |access-date=25 February 2020}}</ref> A 49-year-old man who previously visited Codogno tested positive in [[Pescia]], Tuscany.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Coronavirus Toscana, niente panico: ecco cosa fare |language=Italian |website=la Repubblica |date=25 February 2020 |url= https://firenze.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/25/news/coronavirus_toscana_niente_panico_ecco_cosa_fare-249543095/ |accessdate=25 February 2020}}</ref> Officials in [[Liguria]] confirmed that a 72-year-old female tourist from Castiglione d'Adda tested positive in [[Alassio]] while she was staying in a hotel. The woman was treated at a hospital in [[Genoa]].<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.ansa.it/english/news/general_news/2020/02/25/coronavirus-first-case-in-liguria_263ab67d-5a38-4f81-80bc-4e4ca3b0cc95.html |title=Coronavirus: First case in Liguria |date=25 February 2020 |publisher=ANSA |location=Italy |accessdate=25 February 2020}}</ref> Later in the day, a second case in Liguria was confirmed, a 54-year-old man who had visited Codogno for work and tested positive in [[La Spezia]].<ref name=\"Repubblica_liveupdate\">{{cite web|url=https://www.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/22/news/coronavirus_in_italia_aggiornamento_ora_per_ora-249241616/|title=Coronavirus in Italia: aggiornamento ora per ora|date=22 February 2020|website=la Repubblica|language=it|access-date=24 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Le ultime notizie sul coronavirus in Italia |url=https://www.ilpost.it/2020/03/03/coronavirus-italia-ultime-notizie-aggiornamenti/ |accessdate=4 March 2020 |work=Il Post |date=3 March 2020 |language=it-IT}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |title=Coronavirus, ad Alassio il primo caso in Liguria, interdetti due alberghi, il secondo caso a Spezia |language=Italian |website=la Repubblica |date=25 February 2020 |url= https://genova.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/25/news/coronavirus_primo_caso_anche_in_liguria-249547990/ |accessdate=25 February 2020}}</ref> On 26 February, a 69-year-old man from Lodi with pre-existing medical conditions died in Emilia-Romagna.<ref name=\"TwelfthVictim\">{{Cite news |title=Coronavirus, dodicesima vittima in Italia. Primi contagi tra minori, 6 in Lombardia. Guarita la prima ammalata |language=Italian |work=la Repubblica |date=26 February 2020 |trans-title=Coronavirus, twelfth victim in Italy. First infections among minors, 6 in Lombardy. Heal the first sick woman |url= https://www.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/26/news/coronavirus_contagi_in_nove_regioni_ricciardi_il_95_per_cento_dei_malati_guarisce_-249601102/ |accessdate=26 February 2020}}</ref> The mayor of [[Borgonovo Val Tidone]], Pietro Mazzocchi, tested positive for SARS-CoV-2 and underwent a voluntary isolation at home.<ref>{{Cite news |url= https://www.ctvnews.ca/health/on-the-front-lines-of-coronavirus-with-italy-s-first-sick-mayor-1.4829931 |title=On the front lines of coronavirus with Italy's first sick mayor |last=Feuillatre |first=Cecile |date=27 February 2020 |publisher=CTV News |location=Canaa |accessdate=28 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nAdditional cases involving six minors were identified in Lombardy. A 4-year-old girl from Castiglione d'Adda was admitted to Policlinico San Matteo in Pavia, and a 15-year-old was hospitalised in Seriate Hospital in Bergamo. Two 10-year-olds from [[Cremona]] and Lodi tested positive and were discharged. A 17-year-old from [[Valtellina]] who attended a school in Codogno, and a school friend from [[Sondrio]], also tested positive.<ref name=\":2\" /><ref name=\"TwelfthVictim\" /><ref name=\":3\">{{Cite news |url= https://www.tgcom24.mediaset.it/cronaca/coronavirus-325-i-casi-in-italia-il-contagio-si-allarga-a-9-regioni-11-le-vittime_15336711-202002a.shtml |title=Coronavirus, 12 le vittime in Italia: in Lombardia contagiati anche sei minori \u2013 Guarita la cinese ricoverata allo Spallanzani |website=Tgcom24 |language=Italian |accessdate=26 February 2020}}</ref> Officials in [[Apulia]] confirmed that a 33-year-old man from [[Taranto]], who returned from Codogno on 24 February, tested positive and was admitted to San Giuseppe Moscati Hospital.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Coronavirus, primo paziente positivo in Puglia. \u00c8 un uomo di 43 anni di Taranto tornato da Codogno |language=Italian |work=la Repubblica |date=26 February 2020 |url= https://bari.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/26/news/coronavirus_primo_paziente_positivo_in_puglia_e_un_tarantino_arrivato_da_codogno-249657611/ |accessdate=26 February 2020}}</ref> A close advisor to Lombardy governor [[Attilio Fontana]] tested positive for SARS-CoV-2. Although Fontana tested negative, he decided to put himself in preventive isolation as well.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Coronavirus, positiva collaboratrice di Fontana: il governatore in auto-isolamento. Contagiati anche minori |language=Italian |website=la Repubblica |date=26 February 2020 |url= https://milano.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/26/news/coronavirus_fontana_259_contagiati_anche_minor-249606130/ |accessdate=26 February 2020}}</ref> Officials in Campania confirmed two new cases. A 24-year-old woman from [[Caserta]], who had visited Milan, tested positive. A 25-year-old Ukrainian woman from Cremona, who previously visited Lombardy, tested positive at a hospital in [[Vallo della Lucania]]. Both were transferred to Hospital Domenico Cotugno in [[Naples]], where they underwent isolation.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Coronavirus, dalla Campania due casi positivi: sono due donne giunte dal Nord |language=Italian |work=la Repubblica |date=26 February 2020 |url= https://napoli.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/26/news/coronavirus_dalla_campania_un_tampone_positivo_allo_spallanzani_di_roma-249646115/ |accessdate=26 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 26 February, a woman who had returned from Milan in the days before the emergency in Lombardy had started tested positive for the virus in Catania, Sicily.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Coronavirus, a Catania donna positiva. Borrelli: \"A Palermo guariti due dei tre pazienti\" |language=Italian |work=la Repubblica |date=27 February 2020 |url= https://palermo.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/27/news/coronavirus_a_catania_donna_positiva_tornata_da_milano-249700426/ |accessdate=3 March 2020}}</ref> On 27 February, two 88-year-olds and an 80-year-old died in Lombardy.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Coronavirus in Lombardia, 40 persone guarite. Altri anziani morti. I medici nella zona rossa: \"Noi lasciati soli\" |language=Italian |work=la Repubblica |date=27 February 2020 |url= https://milano.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/27/news/coronavirus_in_lombardia_vertice_tra_i_prefetti_a_fine_settimana_decisione_su_riapertura_scuole_e_stadi-249689409/ |accessdate=27 February 2020}}</ref> Officials in [[Abruzzo]] confirmed that a 50-year-old man from [[Brianza]], Lombardy tested positive and was admitted to the intensive-care unit at Giuseppe Mazzini Hospital at [[Teramo]]. He and his family were staying in his holiday home at [[Roseto degli Abruzzi]].<ref name=\"Repubblica_liveupdate\" /><ref>{{Cite news |title=Coronavirus: primo caso in Abruzzo, \u00e8 un turista Brianza |language=Italian |work=la Repubblica |date=27 February 2020 |url= https://www.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/27/news/coronavirus_primo_caso_in_abruzzo_e_un_turista_brianza-249686482/ |accessdate=27 February 2020}}</ref> On 28 February, four people died, including an 85-year-old Lombardy resident in one of the quarantine zones at a hospital in Piacenza, a 77-year-old and two others over the age of 80.<ref name=\"Repubblica_liveupdate\" /> {{As of|2020|03|01|df=y}}, there were 984 confirmed cases and 73 recoveries in Lombardy.<ref name=\"Repubblica_liveupdate\" /><ref>{{cite news |title=Coronavirus, in Italia 1.694 casi: 41 i morti. I dati regione per regione al 1 marzo |url=https://www.corriere.it/salute/malattie_infettive/20_marzo_01/coronavirus-italia-positivi-sono-1577-34-morti-83-guariti-dati-1-marzo-215bf998-5be0-11ea-ae74-e93752023e91.shtml |accessdate=2 March 2020 |work=Corriere della Sera |date=3 January 2020 |language=it}}</ref> On 4 March, Emilia-Romagna's regional minister of health, Raffaele Donini, and minister for territories, Barbara Lori, were declared positive for COVID-19.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ilfattoquotidiano.it/2020/03/04/coronavirus-la-diretta-positivi-2-assessori-dellemilia-romagna-ce-donini-salute-pronto-nuovo-piano-durgenza-per-terapie-intensive/5724878/|title=Coronavirus, la diretta \u2013 Positivi 2 assessori dell'Emilia-Romagna: c'\u00e8 Donini (Salute). Pronto nuovo piano d'urgenza per terapie intensive|date=4 March 2020|website=Il Fatto Quotidiano}}</ref> Governor [[Stefano Bonaccini]] and the other members of the regional government tested negative.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://bologna.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/03/04/news/coronavirus_positivo_l_assessore_regionale_alla_sanita_donini-250207091/|title=Coronavirus, Emilia Romagna: positivo l'assessore regionale alla Sanit\u00e0 Donini|date=4 March 2020|website=la Repubblica}}</ref>\n\nOn 8 March, Prime Minister [[Giuseppe Conte]] extended the [[quarantine]] lockdown to cover all the region of Lombardy and 14 other [[Northern Italy|northern provinces]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-51787238|title=Coronavirus: Northern Italy quarantines 16 million people|website=BBC|date=8 March 2020}}</ref> On 10 March, Prime Minister Conte increased the quarantine lockdown to cover all of Italy, including travel restrictions and a ban on public gatherings.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-51810673|title=Coronavirus: Italy extends emergency measures nationwide|website=BBC|date=10 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 25 March, the [[Associated Press]] dubbed the [[UEFA Champions League]] match between Bergamo club [[Atalanta B.C.]] and Spanish club [[CF Valencia|Valencia]] at the [[San Siro]] in Milan on 19 February as \"Game Zero\". The match was the first time Atalanta has progressed to a [[2019\u20132020 UEFA Champions League knockout phase|Champions League round of 16 match]], and had an attendance of over 40,000 people \u2013 about one third of Bergamo's population. By 24 March, almost 7,000 people in the [[province of Bergamo]] had tested positive for COVID-19, and more than 1,000 people had died from the virus \u2013 making Bergamo the most hard-hit province in all of Italy during the pandemic.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://apnews.com/ae59cfc0641fc63afd09182bb832ebe2|title=Game Zero: Spread of virus linked to Champions League match|agency=Associated Press|date=25 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n====Veneto====\n[[File:Emergenza Covid19 Ospedale di Padova.jpg|thumb|upright=1.13|[[Protezione Civile|Civil Protection]]'s first aid spot in [[Padua]]]]\nA secondary cluster of infections occurred in the region of Veneto, initially thought to be the result of a farmer being infected when visiting the primary source in Codogno.<ref name=\"urlMailand:NZZ\"/> The farmer was tested, and the following day, the test was confirmed negative.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.padova24ore.it/negativo-al-test-sul-corona-virus-contadino-albettone-joe-formaggio-occorre-senso-responsabilita/|title=Negativo al test sul corona virus il contadino di Albettone. Joe Formaggio: \"Occorre senso di responsabilit\u00e0\"|date=24 February 2020|website=Padova24Ore|language=it-IT|access-date=25 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 21 February 2020, two people tested positive in Veneto. The next day, one of them, a 78-year-old man, died at the Schiavonia Hospital in [[Monselice]], making him the first fatality in Italy. The man lived in the municipality of [[V\u00f2]], which was put under quarantine.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/22/news/adriano_trevisan_la_prima_vittima_di_coronavirus_in_italia-249260446/|title=Adriano Trevisan, la prima vittima di coronavirus in Italia|date=22 February 2020|website=la Repubblica|language=it|access-date=25 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 25 February, a 76-year-old woman with pre-existing medical conditions died in [[Treviso]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tribunatreviso.gelocal.it/treviso/cronaca/2020/02/25/news/primo-caso-di-coronavirus-a-treviso-donna-di-76-anni-in-rianimazione-1.38516066|title=Primo caso di coronavirus a Treviso. Donna di 76 anni in rianimazione|date=25 February 2020|website=Tribuna di Treviso|language=it-IT|access-date=25 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 26 February, an additional case involving a minor was identified. An 8-year-old girl who lived in [[Codevigo]] tested positive.<ref name=\":2\" /><ref name=\":3\" /><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ilgazzettino.it/nordest/venezia/coronavirus_veneto_casi_mappa_contagio_diretta_ultime_notizie-5074003.html|title=Coronavirus: i contagiati sono saliti a 87: nuovi pazienti a Limena, Treviso e Chioggia|website=ilgazzettino.it}}</ref>\n\nOn 28 February, Veneto governor Luca Zaia mentioned that after the first two cases, he ordered all 3,300 V\u00f2 residents to be tested. Of 6,800 swabs, 1.7% were confirmed positive. This epidemiological study would be used for outbreak investigation by the [[University of Padua]].<ref name=\":10\">{{cite web|url=http://www.ansa.it/sito/notizie/cronaca/2020/02/28/zaia-da-test-vo-studio-epidemiologico_2c3d88f3-6a4a-4e00-b255-9e1e2feb2768.html|title=Zaia, da test Vo' studio epidemiologico \u2013 Cronaca|date=28 February 2020|website=Agenzia ANSA|language=it|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nAs of 28 February, there were 151 confirmed cases in Veneto, with 70 cases in the municipality of V\u00f2, including the two fatalities.<ref name=\"Repubblica_liveupdate\" /><ref name=\":10\" />\n\nBy 14 March, no new cases were detected in the municipality of [[V\u00f2]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Coronavirus, a Vo' Euganeo nessun nuovo caso positivo |url=https://www.tgcom24.mediaset.it/cronaca/veneto/coronavirus-a-vo-euganeo-nessun-nuovo-caso-positivo_16143366-202002a.shtml |accessdate=18 March 2020 |work=Tgcom24 |date=14 March 2020 |language=IT}}</ref>\n\n=== Spread to other regions ===\n{{Update section |date=March 2020}}\n[[File:Trasporto di pazienti in bio-contenimento - 7.jpg|thumb|right|upright=1.13|[[Paramedic]]s carrying a patient under [[biocontainment]], in [[Cervia]]]]\n\nA number of cases have emerged in multiple regions that might be isolated and not associated with the Northern Italy clusters.\n\nOn 25 February, the first case in [[Florence]], Tuscany involved a 63-year-old entrepreneur with companies in Asia who had returned from the Philippines and Singapore on 6 January. He tested positive and was admitted to Santa Maria Annunziata Hospital.<ref name=\":2\" /><ref name=\"Repubblica_25Feb_Tuscany\">{{cite web|url=https://www.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/25/news/coronavirus_toscana-249520102/|title=Coronavirus, primi casi a Firenze e a Palermo. 270 casi in Italia. Salgono a 206 in Lombardia e 38 in Veneto|date=25 February 2020|website=la Repubblica|language=it|access-date=25 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe first case in [[Rimini]] involved a 71-year-old man from [[Cattolica]] who returned from Romania on 22 February. He tested positive and was admitted to Infermi Hospital.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://bologna.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/26/news/coronavirus_il_71enne_riminese_risultato_positivo_e_rientrato_dalla_romania-249606750/|title=Coronavirus, il paziente 1 in Romagna \u00e8 un cuoco riminese. Chiuso il ristorante|date=26 February 2020|website=la Repubblica|language=it|access-date=26 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.chiamamicitta.it/coronavirus-a-rimini-venturi-caso-spinoso-paziente-ha-avuto-molti-contatti/|title=Coronavirus, a Rimini caso anomalo. Venturi: \"Paziente ha viaggiato molto\"|date=25 February 2020|website=Chiamamicitta|language=it-IT|access-date=26 February 2020}}</ref> A 51-year-old man from [[Piandimeleto]] who went to Romania with the man also tested positive and underwent self-quarantine at home.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.digi24.ro/stiri/actualitate/un-italian-care-l-a-insotit-in-romania-pe-barbatul-de-71-de-ani-infectat-are-si-el-coronavirus-1266637|title=Primul italian venit \u00een Rom\u00e2nia ar fi infectat cu coronavirus trei persoane \u00een Italia|website=digi24.ro|language=ro|access-date=26 February 2020}}</ref> On 26 February, one of people with whom he had interacted in Romania tested positive.<ref name=\":5\">{{cite web|url=https://www.digi24.ro/stiri/actualitate/primul-caz-de-coronavirus-in-romania-1266806|title=Primul caz de coronavirus \u00een Rom\u00e2nia. Suspiciuni despre un al doilea caz \u00een Gorj|trans-title=First coronavirus case in Romania. Suspicions about a second case in Gorj|language=ro|website=Digi24|access-date=26 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 26 February, the [[Norwegian Institute of Public Health]] confirmed that a 26-year-old Norwegian man living in Florence tested positive and was admitted to Santa Maria Annunziata Hospital. He had stayed in Norway for 14 days and returned to Florence five days before.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.lanazione.it/firenze/cronaca/coronavirus-toscana-1.5046897|title=Coronavirus in Toscana: quattro positivi, altri due casi di contagio a Firenze / DIRETTA|last=Nazione|first=La|date=26 February 2020|website=La Nazione|language=Italian|access-date=26 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thelocal.no/20200226/norwegian-student-tests-positive-for-coronavirus-in-italy|title=Norwegian student tests positive for coronavirus in Italy|website=thelocal.no|access-date=26 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe passenger ferry ''GNV Rhapsody'' was placed under isolation in the port of Genoa with 58 crew members on board after a passenger tested positive for the virus after having sailed to Tunisia on the ship.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.portnews.it/en/coronavirus-gnv-rhapsody-in-isolation/|title=Coronavirus, GNV Rhapsody in isolation|date=4 March 2020|website=PortNews|access-date=10 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 7 March, [[President of Lazio]] and leader of the [[Democratic Party (Italy)|Democratic Party]], [[Nicola Zingaretti]], tested positive for COVID-19.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ilmessaggero.it/roma/news/coronavirus_zingaretti_positivo_nicola_lazio_isolamento_famiglia-5096996.html|title=Coronavirus, Zingaretti positivo: sto bene, sono in isolamento. Controlli sullo staff. La solidariet\u00e0 della politica|accessdate=8 March 2020}}</ref> Ten days before, he was in Milan attending public events.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://milano.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/27/foto/coronavirus_zingaretti_pd_milano-249756747/1/#1|title=\"Milano non-si ferma per il coronavirus\": spritz e tramezzini con il segretario Pd Zingaretti|date=27 February 2020|accessdate=22 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.msn.com/en-us/news/world/italy-pandemic-s-new-epicenter-has-lessons-for-the-world/ar-BB11vMrO?ocid=msedgdhp|title=Italy, Pandemic's New Epicenter, Has Lessons for the World|accessdate=22 March 2020}}</ref> The following day, [[List of presidents of Piedmont|President of Piedmont]] [[Alberto Cirio]] also tested positive.<ref>{{cite news |title=Coronavirus, anche il governatore del Piemonte positivo \u2013 La Stampa |url=https://www.lastampa.it/cronaca/2020/03/08/news/anche-il-governatore-del-piemonte-alberto-cirio-positivo-al-coronavirus-1.38566278 |accessdate=8 March 2020 |work=[[La Stampa]] |date=8 March 2020 |language=it-IT}}</ref>\n\nA US Navy sailor stationed in [[Naples]] tested positive on 6 March. Health officials in the US military began \"a thorough contact investigation\" to determine if any other personnel may have been exposed to the virus.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.cnn.com/2020/03/07/politics/us-navy-sailor-coronavirus-europe/index.html|title=US Navy sailor in Italy tests positive for coronavirus|publisher=CNN|accessdate=8 March 2020|date=7 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 11 March, it was announced that [[Juventus F.C.|Juventus]] and [[Italy national football team|national team]] footballer [[Daniele Rugani]] had tested positive for COVID-19.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/51844945|title=Coronavirus: Juventus centre-back Daniele Rugani tests positive for virus|publisher=BBC|accessdate=11 March 2020|date=11 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nGIMBE (Italy's Group for Evidence-based Medicine), in a report from 18 March, analysed data from the [[Istituto Superiore di Sanit\u00e0]] and found that healthcare workers represented over 8% of all detected coronavirus cases.<ref name=\"aj-oddone-rising-number\">{{cite web |last1=Oddone |first1=Elisa |title=Rising number of medical staff infected with coronavirus in Italy |url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/03/rising-number-medical-staff-infected-coronavirus-italy-200318183939314.html |publisher=[[Al Jazeera]] |accessdate=19 March 2020 |date=18 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 26 March 2020, [[Italica Grondona]] became the world's oldest person to recover successfully from the [[coronavirus]] at the age of 102.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://themalaysianreserve.com/2020/03/30/covid-19-102-year-old-italian-woman-survives-the-virus/|title=COVID-19: 102-year-old Italian woman survives the virus|date=30 March 2020|website=The Malaysian Reserve|access-date=31 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nypost.com/2020/03/29/102-year-old-woman-from-italy-recovers-from-coronavirus/|title=102-year-old woman from Italy recovers from coronavirus|last=Salo|first=Jackie|date=29 March 2020|website=New York Post|access-date=31 March 2020}}</ref> She was successfully recovered from the coronavirus after being tested positive with mild symptoms and was hospitalised in [[Genoa]] on 9 March for 20 days.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://abc7news.com/6063077/|title=102-year-old woman recovers from COVID-19 after 20-day hospitalization in Italy|date=30 March 2020|website=ABC7 San Francisco|access-date=31 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 22 March, it was announced that Juventus forward [[Paulo Dybala]] and former [[Italy national football team|Italy national team]] captain [[Paolo Maldini]] had tested positive for COVID-19.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/51991426|title=Coronavirus: Paulo Dybala and Paolo Maldini test positive|publisher=BBC|accessdate=22 March 2020|date=22 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== Under national lockdown ===\n{{See also|#Nationwide measures}}\nStarting on 8 March, the region of Lombardy together with 14 additional northern and central provinces in Piedmont, Emilia-Romagna, Veneto, and Marche, were put under lockdown.<ref name=\"bbc_lombardy_lockdown\" /> Two days later, the government [[2020 Italy coronavirus lockdown|extended the lockdown measures to the whole country]].<ref name=\"cnn_italy_lockdown\" />\n\nTwo weeks later, the number of new cases per day started to show signs of slowing down, while the number of new deaths rose slightly.<ref>{{cite news |title=Italy's coronavirus deaths rise slightly, but new cases continue to slow |url=https://www.thelocal.it/20200330/latest-coronavirus-deaths-italy |accessdate=7 April 2020 |work=The Local.it |date=30 March 2020}}</ref>\nOn 31 March, the president of the Italian National Institute of Health, Silvio Brusaferro, announced that the pandemic had reached its peak in the country.<ref>{{cite news |title=\"L'Italia ha raggiunto il picco\", dice l'Istituto Superiore di Sanit\u00e0 |url=https://www.agi.it/cronaca/news/2020-03-31/coronavirus-istituto-superiore-sanit-picco-8038210/ |accessdate=7 April 2020 |work=Agi |date=31 March 2020 |language=it}}</ref> The news was confirmed also by the head of the Civil Protection, Angelo Borrelli.<ref>{{cite news |title=Coronavirus, Borrelli: Raggiunto il picco ma non abbassare la guardia - Salute & Benessere |url=https://www.ansa.it/canale_saluteebenessere/notizie/sanita/2020/03/30/coronavirus-curva-contagi-italia-lombardia-guariti-bandiere-lutto_947f659c-647e-4242-ac48-e2b793e46846.html |accessdate=7 April 2020 |work=ANSA |date=30 March 2020 |language=it}}</ref>\n\nThree weeks into the lockdown, its effects began to show. Italy reported declines in the number of new cases and of new deaths per day. The country also saw a steady decrease in the occupancy of intensive care units.<ref>{{cite news |title=LATEST: Pressure on Italy's intensive care wards eases as new coronavirus cases slow again |url=https://www.thelocal.it/20200406/latest-coronavirus-numbers-italy |accessdate=7 April 2020 |work=The Local.it |date=6 April 2020}}</ref> On 5 April, Italy had the lowest number of new daily deaths in two and a half weeks,<ref>{{cite news |last1=Colten |first1=Jerrold |last2=Orihuela |first2=Rodrigo |title=Europe's Slowing Virus Deaths Bolster Leaders on Lockdowns |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2020-04-05/italy-reports-lowest-daily-coronavirus-fatalities-since-march-19 |accessdate=7 April 2020 |work=Bloomberg |date=5 April 2020}}</ref> and one day later the lowest number of new daily cases in three weeks.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Follain |first1=John |title=Italy Reports Lowest New Virus Infections in Almost Three Weeks |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2020-04-06/italy-reports-lowest-new-virus-infections-in-almost-three-weeks |accessdate=7 April 2020 |work=Bloomberg |date=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Management==\n\n===First measures===\nOn 31 January 2020, the [[Council of Ministers of Italy|Italian Council of Ministers]] appointed [[Angelo Borrelli]], head of the [[Protezione Civile|Civil Protection]], as Special Commissioner for the COVID-19 emergency.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tg24.sky.it/politica/approfondimenti/angelo-borrelli-chi-e.html|title=Chi \u00e8 Angelo Borrelli, capo della protezione civile nominato commissario per l'emergenza coronavirus &#124; Sky TG24|website=tg24.sky.it}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fanpage.it/politica/coronavirus-angelo-borrelli-nominato-commissario-straordinario-ecco-chi-e/|title=Coronavirus, Angelo Borrelli commissario straordinario: potr\u00e0 anche requisire gli hotel|website=Fanpage}}</ref>\n\n[[File:2020 coronavirus task force.jpg|thumb|upright=1.13|[[Conte II Cabinet|Italian government]] task force to face the COVID-19 outbreak in the [[Protezione Civile|Civil Protection]] situation room on 23 February. Prime Minister [[Giuseppe Conte]] and Health Minister [[Roberto Speranza]] are in the foreground, from behind.]]\n\nOn 22 February, [[Conte II Cabinet|the government]] announced a new decree imposing the quarantine of more than 50,000 people from 11 different municipalities in [[Northern Italy]]. The quarantine zones are called the Red Zones and the areas in Lombardy and Veneto outside of them are called the Yellow Zones.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://milano.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/21/news/coronavirus_codogno_castiglione_d_adda_contagiati_misure_sicurezza-249154447/|title=Coronavirus, in dieci comuni lombardi: 50 mila persone costrette a restare in casa. Quarantena all'ospedale milanese di Baggio|date=21 February 2020|website=la Repubblica|language=it|access-date=23 February 2020}}</ref> Penalties for violations range from a \u20ac206 fine to three months of imprisonment.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ilsole24ore.com/art/coronavirus-chi-viola-quarantena-rischia-l-arresto-fino-tre-mesi-ACrcnLLB|title=Coronavirus, come funziona la quarantena e cosa rischia chi la viola (l'arresto)|website=Il Sole 24 ORE}}</ref> The [[Italian army|Italian military]] and law enforcement agencies were instructed to secure and implement the lockdown.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-51602007|title=Venice Carnival closes amid coronavirus outbreak|date=23 February 2020|publisher=BBC}}</ref>\n\nSchools were closed in ten municipalities in Lombardy, one in Veneto and one in Emilia Romagna. All public events were cancelled and some commercial activities{{which|date=February 2020}} were halted or were allowed to resume only until 6&nbsp;pm.<ref name=\"Facebook_Pavia\">{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/comunePV/posts/2439843176121889|title=Comune di Pavia|website=facebook.com|access-date=23 February 2020}}{{Primary source inline|date=February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.corriere.it/cronache/20_febbraio_21/scuole-chiuse-il-coronavirus-lombardia-lodi-piacenza-codogno-a190ccee-54bd-11ea-9196-da7d305401b7.shtml|title=Quali sono i Comuni che hanno chiuso le scuole per il Coronavirus|last=online|first=Redazione|date=21 February 2020|website=Corriere della Sera|language=it|access-date=23 February 2020}}</ref> All religious services were cancelled.<ref name=\"Repubblica_23Feb_Carnival\">{{cite web|url=https://www.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/23/news/coronavirus_scuole_chiuse_e_niente_carnevale_tutti_i_provvedimenti-249355737/|title=Coronavirus, scuole chiuse e niente Carnevale di Venezia. I provvedimenti Regione per Regione|date=23 February 2020|website=la Repubblica|language=it|access-date=25 February 2020}}</ref> Regional train services to the most affected areas were suspended, with trains skipping stops at Codogno, [[Maleo, Lombardy|Maleo]] and Casalpusterlengo stations.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.corriere.it/cronache/20_febbraio_22/coronavirus-treni-fermi-ore-lecce-milano-nessuno-stop-comuni-rischio-lodigiano-431e997c-553d-11ea-8418-2150c9ca483e.shtml|title=Coronavirus, treni fermi per ore a Lecce e Milano. I convogli non-fermano nei Comuni a rischio del Lodigiano|last=online|first=Redazione|date=22 February 2020|website=Corriere della Sera|language=it|access-date=23 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://milano.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/22/news/coronavirus_il_comune_di_milano_sospende_dal_lavoro_i_dipendenti_che_abitano_delle_zone_coinvolte-249252812/|title=Coronavirus, per una settimana didattica sospesa nelle universit\u00e0 lombarde. Comune di Milano e grandi aziende: i lavoratori a rischio restano a casa|date=22 February 2020|website=la Repubblica|language=it|access-date=23 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nPeople with symptoms were advised to call the [[112 (emergency telephone number)|112]] emergency number, instead of going directly to hospitals, in an effort to limit the disease's spread.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sanmatteo.org/site/home/area-comunicazione/in-primo-piano.html|title=Coronavirus, aggiornamenti ed avvisi \u2013 Policlinico San Matteo Pavia Fondazione IRCCS|website=sanmatteo.org|language=it|access-date=23 February 2020}}</ref> The [[Ministry of Health (Italy)|Ministry of Health]] provided a website and a direct line (1500) from which people could obtain the latest updates and information, as well as report suspected cases.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.salute.gov.it/nuovocoronavirus|title=Nuovo coronavirus|last=Salute|first=Ministero della|website=salute.gov.it|language=IT|access-date=23 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nEducational trips to destinations in Italy and abroad were suspended. Universities in Lombardy, Veneto, [[Trentino Alto-Adige]], Piedmont and [[Emilia-Romagna]] suspended all activities from 23 February until 1 March.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.unipv.it/?p=46130|title=news.unipv \u2013 Coronavirus: Sospensione delle attivit\u00e0 didattiche dal 24/2 all'1/03|website=news.unipv|language=it-IT|access-date=23 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.unimi.it/it/coronavirus-misure-urgenti-la-comunita-universitaria|title=Coronavirus: misure urgenti per la comunit\u00e0 universitaria {{!}} Universit\u00e0 degli Studi di Milano Statale|website=unimi.it|access-date=23 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.unibg.it/node/9238|title=Sospensione precauzionale delle attivit\u00e0 didattiche |publisher=Universit\u00e0 degli studi di Bergamo |access-date=23 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.unive.it/pag/14024/?tx_news_pi1%5Bnews%5D=8621&cHash=aa65321bb25bdccbf08c0c18299d48de|title=Coronavirus: lezioni ed esami sospesi dal 24/02 al 29/02|website=Universit\u00e0 Ca' Foscari Venezia|language=it|access-date=23 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.unito.it/avvisi/coronavirus-aggiornamenti-sulla-gestione-della-situazione|title=Coronavirus: aggiornamenti sulla gestione della situazione|date=23 February 2020|website=Universit\u00e0 di Torino|language=it|access-date=23 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://magazine.unibo.it/archivio/2020/coronavirus-sospensione-attivita-didattica-e-misure-precauzionali-contro-la-diffusione-dell2019infezione|title=Coronavirus: Sospensione Attivit\u00e0 Didattica e misure precauzionali contro la diffusione dell'infezione|website=magazine.unibo.it|language=it|access-date=23 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 22 February 2020, Prime Minister [[Giuseppe Conte]] suspended all sporting events in the regions of Lombardy and Veneto, which included three [[Serie A]] football matches in those regions, as well as one in [[Piedmont]], that were to be played the following day.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.football-italia.net/150398/serie-games-suspended-coronavirus|title=Serie A games suspended for Coronavirus|publisher=Football Italia|date=22 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.football-italia.net/150407/coronavirus-also-cancels-torino-parma|title=Coronavirus also cancels Torino-Parma|publisher=Football Italia|date=23 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2020/feb/23/three-serie-a-matches-coronavirus-outbreak-inter-milan|title=Four Serie A matches called off due to coronavirus outbreak|date=23 February 2020 |work=The Guardian}}</ref> The following week, six Serie A matches were initially to be played behind closed doors, but all were later suspended,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/51637700|title=Coronavirus: Five Serie A matches to be played behind closed doors|publisher=bbc.com|date=25 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.football-italia.net/150647/official-juventus-inter-and-others-moved|title=Official: Juventus-Inter called off and others|publisher=Football Italia|date=29 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.football-italia.net/150715/official-sampdoria-verona|title=Official: Sampdoria-Verona is off|publisher=Football Italia|date=1 March 2020}}</ref> as were two [[Coppa Italia]] matches.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.football-italia.net/150787/official-juventus-milan-postponed|title=Official: Juventus-Milan postponed|publisher=Football Italia|date=3 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.football-italia.net/150804/official-napoli-inter-postponed|title=Official: Napoli-Inter postponed|publisher=Football Italia|date=4 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nAuthorities in Veneto cancelled the last two days of the [[Carnival of Venice]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-51602007|title=Venice Carnival closes amid coronavirus outbreak|date=23 February 2020|work=BBC News|access-date=23 February 2020}}</ref> Authorities in Piedmont cancelled the last three days of the Carnival of [[Ivrea]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.lastampa.it/cronaca/2020/02/24/news/ivrea-addio-guerra-delle-arance-e-la-quarta-volta-nella-storia-1.38507893|title=Ivrea, addio guerra delle arance. \u00c8 la quarta volta nella storia|date=2