solati_no_il_racconto_dei_liceali_di_parma_dalle_loro_camere-249616316/|title=Coronavirus, \"Confinati s\u00ec, isolati no\": il racconto dei liceali di Parma dalle loro camere|date=26 February 2020|website=la Repubblica|language=it|access-date=26 February 2020}}</ref> The [[University of Palermo]] suspended all activities until 9 March.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://livesicilia.it/2020/02/25/universita-lezioni-sospese-e-lauree-a-porte-chiuse_1120700/|title=Universit\u00e0, lezioni sospese e lauree a porte chiuse|website=Live Sicilia|language=it|access-date=25 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n[[Morgan Stanley]], [[Barclays]], [[Mediobanca]] and [[UniCredit]] requested their Milan staff to work from home.<ref name=\"Reuters_banks\" />\n\nMultiple fairs and exhibitions were rescheduled. Salone del Mobile, a furniture fair in Milan, was postponed to 16 to 21 June.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ilsole24ore.com/art/coronavirus-salone-mobile-rinviato-giugno-AClPZvLB|title=Coronavirus, Salone del Mobile rinviato a giugno|website=Il Sole 24 ORE|language=it|access-date=25 February 2020}}</ref> Bologna Children's Book Fair was rescheduled to 4 to 7 May.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bookfair.bolognafiere.it/|title=Bologna Children's Book Fair|last=Fiere|first=Bologna|website=Bologna Children bookfair|access-date=25 February 2020}}</ref> Cosmoprof Worldwide Bologna, a cosmetic fair, was rescheduled to 11 to 15 June.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cosmoprof.com/en/official-updates/|title=Official updates|last=COSMOPROF|website=COSMOPROF|access-date=25 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200225201203/https://www.cosmoprof.com/en/official-updates/|archive-date=25 February 2020|url-status=dead}}</ref> Expocasa, a furniture fair in Turin, was rescheduled initially to 28 March to 5 April but later to future date to be announced later.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://torino.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/25/news/coronavirus_expocasa_rinviata_la_fiera_dell_arredamento_si_terra_dal_28_marzo_al_5_aprile-249565043/|title=Coronavirus, Expocasa rinviata, la fiera dell'arredamento si terr\u00e0 dal 28 marzo al 5 aprile|date=25 February 2020|website=la Repubblica|language=it|access-date=25 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=AGGIORNAMENTI CORONA VIRUS \u2013 RINVIO MANIFESTAZIONE |url=https://www.expocasa.it/3796/aggiornamenti-corona-virus |website=EXPOCASA |accessdate=20 March 2020}}</ref> Roma Motodays was postponed to 17 to 19 April.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.repubblica.it/motori/sezioni/moto/2020/02/25/news/motodays_coronavirus_rinvio-249562967/|title=Effetto Coronavirus: rinviato a Roma il Motodays|date=25 February 2020|website=la Repubblica|language=it|access-date=25 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nItaly opened a probe into skyrocketing online prices for masks and sanitising gels. Police issued warnings that criminals were using false identities and posing as health inspectors to gain access to people's homes to steal money, jewellery and other valuables.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/china-health-italy-probe-idUSL5N2AP37X|title=Italy probes \"insane\" prices for coronavirus masks, sanitizers|date=25 February 2020|agency=Reuters|access-date=25 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 26 February, Director of the Italian National Institute of Health Franco Locatelli announced that swabbing would only be performed on symptomatic patients, as 95% of the swabs previously tested were negative.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tg24.sky.it/cronaca/2020/02/26/coronavirus-tamponi-solo-su-sintomatici.html|title=Coronavirus, Consiglio superiore sanit\u00e0: tamponi solo su sintomatici {{!}} Sky TG24|website=tg24.sky.it|access-date=26 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe [[Italian Minister of University and Research]], [[Gaetano Manfredi]], announced that online lessons would be delivered to students in areas affected by the outbreak starting on 2 March.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.miur.gov.it/web/guest/-/coronavirus-manfredi-universita-da-lunedi-lezioni-on-line-per-gli-studenti-delle-aree-colpite-primo-passo-verso-la-normalita-|title=Coronavirus, Manfredi, Universit\u00e0: \"Da luned\u00ec lezioni on line per gli studenti delle aree colpite, primo passo verso la normalit\u00e0\" \u2013 Coronavirus, Manfredi, Universit\u00e0: \"Da luned\u00ec lezioni on line per gli studenti delle aree colpite, primo passo verso la normalit\u00e0\"|website=Miur \u2013 Ministero dell'istruzione \u2013 Ministero dell'universit\u00e0 e della ricerca|language=it-IT|access-date=27 February 2020}}</ref> [[Palermo]] and [[Naples]] closed all schools until 29 February.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://napoli.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/26/news/coronavirus_a_napoli_scuole_chiuse_fino_a_sabato-249615433/|title=Coronavirus: a Napoli scuole chiuse fino a sabato 29 febbraio|date=26 February 2020|website=la Repubblica|language=it|access-date=26 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.blogsicilia.it/palermo/coronavirus-scuole-chiuse-palermo-ordinanza-regione/520347/|title=Scuole chiuse fino a luned\u00ec a Palermo e Provincia, arriva l'ordinanza regionale|date=25 February 2020|website=BlogSicilia \u2013 Ultime notizie dalla Sicilia|language=it-IT|access-date=26 February 2020}}</ref> The [[University of Basilicata]] installed a thermal scanner and continued all teaching activities as per normal.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ansa.it/basilicata/notizie/2020/02/26/coronavirus-scanner-termico-allunibas_1147963f-0e34-4dbe-96a9-4e76a15b5264.html|title=Coronavirus: scanner termico all'Unibas \u2013 Basilicata|date=26 February 2020|website=Agenzia ANSA|language=it|access-date=26 February 2020}}</ref> The [[University of Bari]] suspended all medical- and health-related internships for medical and healthcare students.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://bari.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/26/news/coronavirus_sospesi_i_tirocini_per_gli_studenti_di_medicina_di_bari-249627906/|title=Coronavirus, sospesi i tirocini di Medicina a Bari. Gli studenti: \"Spiegateci il perch\u00e9\"|date=26 February 2020|website=la Repubblica|language=it|access-date=26 February 2020}}</ref> [[Polytechnic University of Milan|Politecnico di Milano]] conducted thesis mentoring for more than one thousand students graduating the following week using [[Skype]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://milano.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/26/news/coronavirus_in_lombardia_al_politecnico_di_milano_la_tesi_di_laurea_si_discute_via_skype-249628719/|title=Coronavirus in Lombardia, al Politecnico di Milano la tesi di laurea si discute via Skype|date=26 February 2020|website=la Repubblica|language=it|access-date=26 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Covid Sign.jpg|thumb|upright=1.13|A sign in [[Bologna]], advising the closure of all museums in the city due to the outbreak]]\nThe [[Italian Winter Sports Federation]] decided to proceed with the Women's World Cup alpine skiing races at [[La Thuile, Aosta Valley]] on 29 February.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://torino.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/26/news/coronavirus_confermate_le_gare_della_coppa_del_mondo_di_sci_femminile_a_la_thuile-249617192/|title=Coronavirus, confermate le gare della coppa del mondo di sci femminile a La Thuile|date=26 February 2020|website=la Repubblica|language=it|access-date=26 February 2020}}</ref> The MIDO Milan Eyewear Show was rescheduled to 5 to 7 July.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wmido.com/ita-la-50a-edizione-di-mido-si-terra-dal-5-al-7-luglio/|title=MIDO 2020 will take place from July 5 to the 7 at Rho Fiera Milano \u2013 WMido|website=wmido.com|access-date=26 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 27 February, [[Taranto]], Apulia closed all schools until 29 February.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.primocircolotaranto.gov.it/wordpress/ordinanza-n-13-comune-di-taranto-chiusura-scuole-per-le-giornate-del-27-28-e-29-febbraio-2020/|title=Ordinanza n. 13 -Comune di Taranto chiusura scuole per le giornate del 27 28 e 29 febbraio 2020 \u2013 Istituto Comprensivo Renato Moro|language=it-IT|access-date=27 February 2020}}</ref> Multiple schools were closed in Roseto degli Abruzzi.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.abruzzolive.it/coronavirus-turista-positivo-chiuse-scuole-a-roseto-in-ricostruzione-movimenti-del-paziente-brianzolo/|title=Coronavirus, turista positivo: chiuse scuole a Roseto. In ricostruzione movimenti del paziente brianzolo|website=AbruzzoLive|language=it-IT|access-date=27 February 2020}}</ref> [[D'Annunzio University of Chieti\u2013Pescara|D'Annunzio University]] suspended all activities until 29 February.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.scuolainforma.it/2020/02/26/aggiornamento-coronavirus-al-26-2-per-ogni-regione-altre-scuole-chiuse-nuovo-decreto.html|title=Aggiornamento Coronavirus al 26/2 per ogni regione: altre scuole chiuse, decreto con nuove misure|date=26 February 2020|website=ScuolaInforma|language=it-IT|access-date=27 February 2020}}</ref> Cartoocomics Fair in Milan was rescheduled to 2 to 4 October.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://it.finance.yahoo.com/notizie/coronavirus-fiera-milano-posticipa-cartoomics-al-2-4-104522157.html|title=Coronavirus, Fiera Milano posticipa Cartoomics al 2\u20134 ottobre|publisher=Yahoo! Finance|language=it-IT|access-date=27 February 2020}}</ref> The Winter Rescue Race in [[Piedmont]] was cancelled.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.unionemonregalese.it/2020/02/27/annullata-coronavirus-winter-rescue-race-artesina/|title=Artesina: le gare di Soccorso alpino annullate per l'emergenza coronavirus|last=Monregalese|first=Redazione Unione|date=27 February 2020|website=L'Unione Monregalese|language=it-IT|access-date=27 February 2020}}</ref> [[University of Bologna]] planned to set up a remote teaching project in which exams and lessons would be delivered to students online, to be partially completed on 2 March.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://bologna.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/27/news/coronavirus_universita_di_bologna_lezioni_esami_e_lauree_on_line-249716958/|title=Coronavirus, Universit\u00e0 di Bologna: lezioni, esami e lauree on line|date=27 February 2020|website=la Repubblica|language=it|access-date=27 February 2020}}</ref> [[Messina]] closed all schools from 29 February to 3 March.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.strettoweb.com/2020/02/coronavirus-messina-scuole/976298/|title=Messina, scuole chiuse per il Coronavirus: ecco l'ordinanza del sindaco|date=27 February 2020|website=Stretto Web|language=it-IT|access-date=27 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 28 February, during an interview with [[Rai News24]], Professor Massimo Galli from the Luigi Sacco Hospital in Milan suggested that the majority of newly recorded cases were pre-existing cases that were finally detected during the extensive tests performed on people (and their relatives) who had come in contact with confirmed patients.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rainews.it/dl/rainews/media/ContentItem-81824682-be63-4c83-a220-ae2b5630732b.html|title=Massimo Galli: il virus circolava gi\u00e0 prima dei casi conclamati|website=Rainews|language=italian|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref> The rapid increase of positive cases was the result of the blanket testing approach that was deployed following the first confirmed case in Codogno.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/28/news/_polmoniti_anomale_a_meta_gennaio_cosi_e_nato_il_focolaio_di_codogno_-249759796/|title=Coronavirus, polmoniti anomale a met\u00e0 gennaio: \"Cos\u00ec \u00e8 nato il focolaio di Codogno\"|date=27 February 2020|website=la Repubblica|language=it|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe Ministry of Health announced new guidelines for reporting cases. It would no longer report asymptomatic cases (positive swabs taken from patients who were not showing symptoms), which had counted as 40 to 50% of all reported cases at the time. These people would undergo isolation at home and would be followed up with new tests until they were negative.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/28/news/cambia_il_metodo_di_conteggio_esclusi_i_positivi_asintomatici-249765660/|title=Cambia il metodo di conteggio: esclusi i positivi asintomatici|date=27 February 2020|website=la Repubblica|language=it|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://abcnews.go.com/Health/wireStory/italy-virus-count-methods-agencys-urging-69254949|title=Italy blasts virus panic as it eyes new testing criteria|website=ABC News|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref> Universities in Lombardy extended their closure until 7 March.<ref name=\"Repubblica_liveupdate\" />\n\n===Nationwide measures===\nOn 1 March, the Council of Ministers approved a decree to organise the containment of the outbreak. In the decree, the Italian national territory was divided into three areas:<ref>{{cite news |title=Il governo firma il decreto coronavirus: l'Italia divisa in 3 zone |url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2020/03/01/news/coronavirus_misure_governo-249980561/ |accessdate=2 March 2020 |work=la Repubblica |date=1 March 2020 |language=it}}</ref>\n* A red zone (composed of the municipalities of Bertonico, Casalpusterlengo, Castelgerundo, Castiglione D'Adda, Codogno, Fombio, Maleo, San Fiorano, Somaglia and Terranova dei Passerini in Lombardy, and the municipality of V\u00f2 in Veneto), where the whole population is in quarantine.\n* A yellow zone (composed of the regions of Lombardy, Veneto and Emilia-Romagna), where social and sport events are suspended and schools, theatres, clubs and cinemas are closed.\n* The rest of the national territory, where safety and prevention measures are advertised in public places and special sanitisations are performed on means of public transport.\n\n[[File:COVID19 avvisi a Bologna.jpg|left|thumb|Montage of notices on shops in Bologna declaring their temporary closure, or requiring people to stay at least one metre apart]]\nOn 4 March, the Italian government imposed the shutdown of all schools and universities nationwide for two weeks as the country reached 100 deaths from the outbreak.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Guerzoni |first1=Monica |title=Scuole e universit\u00e0 di tutta Italia chiuse fino a met\u00e0 marzo per il coronavirus |url=https://www.corriere.it/scuola/20_marzo_04/coronavirus-scuole-chiuse-tutta-italia-decisione-governo-entro-stasera-e7ba0614-5e12-11ea-8e26-25d9a5210d01.shtml |accessdate=4 March 2020 |work=Corriere della Sera |date=3 April 2020 |language=it}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last=Palermo|first=Angela Giuffrida Lorenzo Tondo in|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/04/italy-orders-closure-of-schools-and-universities-due-to-coronavirus|title=Italy orders closure of all schools and universities due to coronavirus|date=4 March 2020|work=The Guardian|access-date=5 March 2020|last2=Beaumont|first2=Peter|issn=0261-3077}}</ref> The same day, the government ruled that all sporting events in Italy would be played behind closed doors until 3 April.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.football-italia.net/150823/official-behind-closed-doors-until-april-3|title=Official: Behind closed doors until April 3|publisher=Football Italia|date=4 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 5 March, when the newly appointed [[Emilia-Romagna]] regional minister of health, Raffale Donini, tested positive for COVID-19, Governor [[Stefano Bonaccini]] appointed Sergio Venturi as commissioner for the emergency. Venturi was the regional minister of health until February 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://gazzettadireggio.gelocal.it/reggio/cronaca/2020/03/05/news/coronavirus-positivo-l-assessore-donini-torna-in-campo-l-ex-venturi-1.38553828|title=Coronavirus, positivo l'assessore Donini: torna in campo l'ex Venturi &#124; A Reggio Emilia undici casi in pi\u00f9: adesso sono 31|date=5 March 2020|website=Gazzetta di Reggio|accessdate=8 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn the night between 7 and 8 March, the government approved a decree to lock down Lombardy and 14 other provinces in Veneto, Emilia-Romagna, Piedmont and Marche, involving more than 16&nbsp;million people.<ref name=\"bbc_lombardy_lockdown\">{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-51787238|title=Northern Italy quarantines 16 million people|work=BBC News|date=8 March 2020|accessdate=8 March 2020|via=bbc.com}}</ref> The decree \"absolutely avoided any movement into and out of the areas\" and, like the previous one, it provided sanctions of up to three months in prison for those who violated the lockdown.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/italy-plans-large-scale-lockdown-in-countrys-north-to-fight-coronavirus-11583613874|title=Italy Locks Down the Country's North to Fight Coronavirus|first=Eric Sylvers and Giovanni|last=Legorano|date=8 March 2020|accessdate=8 March 2020|work=The Wall Street Journal}}</ref> It was possible to move into and out of the areas only for emergencies or \"proven working needs\", which must be authorised by the [[prefect]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/03/08/news/coronavirus_i_decreti_del_governo-250617415/|title=Coronavirus, il decreto del governo: tutte le misure per la zona arancione e quelle per il resto d'Italia|date=8 March 2020|website=la Repubblica|accessdate=8 March 2020}}</ref> The decree also established the closure of all gyms, swimming pools, spas and wellness centres. Shopping centres had to be closed on weekends, while other commercial activities could remain open if a distance of one metre between customers could be guaranteed.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.romatoday.it/attualita/coronavirus-pub-cinema-teatri-locali-chiusi-nuovo-decreto.html|title=Coronavirus: stop a pub, cinema, teatro e discoteche anche a Roma. Ecco cosa prevede il nuovo decreto|website=RomaToday|language=it|access-date=8 March 2020}}</ref> The decree imposed the closure of museums, cultural centres and ski resorts in the lockdown areas and the closure of cinemas, theatres, pubs, dance schools, game rooms, betting rooms and [[Bingo (American version)|bingo]] halls, [[disco]]s and similar places in the entire country.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.romatoday.it/attualita/coronavirus-pub-cinema-teatri-locali-chiusi-nuovo-decreto.html|title=Coronavirus: stop a pub, cinema, teatro e discoteche anche a Roma. Ecco cosa prevede il nuovo decreto|website=RomaToday|accessdate=8 March 2020}}</ref> Civil and religious ceremonies, including funeral ceremonies, were suspended. All organised events were also suspended, as well as events in public or private places, including those of a cultural, recreational, sporting and religious nature, even if held in closed places.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://corrieredellumbria.corr.it/news/coronavirus/1516428/emergenza-coronavirus-bozza-decreto-sospesi-anche--funerali-in-lombardia-e-11-province-covi19-epidemia-contagio.html|title=Emergenza Coronavirus, bozza decreto: sospesi anche i funerali in Lombardia e 11 province|accessdate=8 March 2020}}</ref> This measure was described as the largest lockdown in the history of Europe,<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/03/08/world/europe/italy-coronavirus-quarantine.html|title=On Day 1 of Lockdown, Italian Officials Urge Citizens to Abide by Rules|first1=Jason|last1=Horowitz|first2=Emma|last2=Bubola|date=8 March 2020|accessdate=10 March 2020|work=The New York Times}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theverge.com/2020/3/7/21169637/italy-lockdown-lombardy-coronavirus-outbreak|title=Italy locks down northern region in response to coronavirus outbreak|first=Kim|last=Lyons|date=7 March 2020|website=The Verge|accessdate=8 March 2020}}</ref> as well as the most aggressive response taken in any region beyond China, and paralysed the wealthiest parts of the country as Italy attempted to constrain the rapid spread of the disease.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Horowitz |first1=Jason |title=Italy Locks Down Much of the Country's North Over the Coronavirus |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/03/07/world/europe/coronavirus-italy.html|accessdate=8 March 2020 |work=The New York Times |date=7 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=Italia>[https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/europe/italy-coronavirus-milan-lombardy-lockdowns/2020/03/07/403fcea2-60b3-11ea-ac50-18701e14e06d_story.html To contain coronavirus, Italy will restrict movement across much of its northern region, including the city of Milan], ''[[The Washington Post]]'', Chico Harlan and Stefano Pitrelli, 7 March 2020. Retrieved 8 March 2020.</ref>\n\nRiots broke out in many penitentiaries throughout Italy after restrictions on [[conjugal visit]]s were imposed by the government in the 8 March decree.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.timesofisrael.com/liveblog_entry/italian-prisoners-riot-over-coronavirus-restrictions/|title=Italian prisoners riot over coronavirus restrictions|website=The Times of Israel|accessdate=10 March 2020}}</ref> Nine prisoners died in [[Modena]] and three in [[Rieti]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://bologna.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/03/09/news/modena_sei_morti_nella_rivolta_in_carcere-250719903/|title=Modena, sette detenuti morti nella rivolta in carcere e sei in prognosi riservata|date=9 March 2020|website=la Repubblica|accessdate=10 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/03/10/news/coronavirus_carceri_ancora_proteste_tre_detenuti_morti_a_rieti-250829816/|title=Coronavirus, carceri, ancora proteste. Tre detenuti morti a Rieti, le vittime salgono a dodici|date=10 March 2020|website=la Repubblica|accessdate=11 March 2020}}</ref> while 76 detainees escaped from [[Foggia]]'s penitentiary.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ansa.it/sito/notizie/cronaca/2020/03/09/rivolta-in-carcere-foggiaalcuni-evadono_1e2d031d-d354-4076-8129-bdccaed5fa23.html|title=Rivolta in carcere Foggia,alcuni evadono \u2013 Cronaca|date=9 March 2020|website=Agenzia ANSA|accessdate=10 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://bari.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/03/09/news/coronavirus_detenuti_evadono_dal_carcere_di_foggia_e_vengono_bloccati_all_esterno-250720580/|title=Coronavirus, rivolta nelle carceri: a Foggia evasione di massa. A Trani e Bari strade bloccate|date=9 March 2020|website=la Repubblica|accessdate=10 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://abcnews.go.com/Health/wireStory/italian-inmates-die-protest-virus-measures-69482325|title=Prison riots hit Italy amid virus; 6 die in overdose|date=9 March 2020|work=ABC News|accessdate=10 March 2020}}</ref> Two prison agents were assaulted and kidnapped in [[Pavia]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ilfattoquotidiano.it/2020/03/08/coronavirus-rivolta-nelle-carceri-a-pavia-sequestrati-2-agenti-modena-morto-un-detenuto-proteste-pure-a-frosinone-napoli-e-palermo/5729730/|title=Coronavirus, rivolta nelle carceri: a Pavia sequestrati 2 agenti. Modena, morti tre detenuti. Proteste pure a Frosinone, Napoli e Palermo|date=8 March 2020|website=Il Fatto Quotidiano|accessdate=10 March 2020}}</ref> On 9 March in [[Bologna]], detainees took control of the Dozza penitentiary, forcing personnel to exit the building.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/search/top/?q=\u00e8tv&epa=SEARCH_BOX|title=Rivolta anche al carcere di Bologna|accessdate=10 March 2020}}{{Primary source inline|date=April 2020}}</ref> On 11 March, two prisoners were found dead in Bologna's penitentiary.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://bologna.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/03/11/news/detenuto_morto_dozza-250944868/|title=Rivolta nel carcere di Bologna: morto un detenuto|date=11 March 2020|website=la Repubblica|accessdate=12 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 9 March, the government announced that all sporting events in Italy would be cancelled until at least 3 April, but the ban does not include Italian clubs or national teams participating in international competitions.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/51808683|title=Coronavirus: All sport in Italy to be suspended because of outbreak|date=9 March 2020|work=BBC Sport|access-date=9 March 2020}}</ref> In the evening, Conte announced in a press conference that all measures previously applied only in the so-called \"red zones\" had been extended to the whole country, putting approximately 60 million people in lockdown. Conte later proceeded to officially sign the new executive decree.<ref name=\"cnn_italy_lockdown\">{{cite news |last1=Reynolds |first1=Emma |last2=Picheta |first2=Rob |title=All of Italy is in lockdown as coronavirus cases rise |url=https://edition.cnn.com/2020/03/09/europe/coronavirus-italy-lockdown-intl/index.html |accessdate=9 March 2020 |publisher=CNN |date=9 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Tondo |first1=Lorenzo |title=Coronavirus: Italian PM extends lockdown to entire country |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/09/coronavirus-italy-prime-minister-country-lockdown?utm_term=Autofeed&CMP=twt_gu&utm_medium&utm_source=Twitter#Echobox=1583793579 |accessdate=9 March 2020 |work=The Guardian |date=9 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Ian Art Photography - Italy 100 people queuing at a supermarket during coronavirus outbreak mar-2020.jpg|thumb|upright=1.13|Queue in front of a supermarket after the introduction of [[social distancing]] rules]]\nOn 11 March, the government allocated 25&nbsp;billion euros for the emergency.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.repubblica.it/economia/2020/03/11/news/emergenza_coronavirus_conferenza_stampa_conte_misure_economiche-250924846/|title=Emergenza coronavirus, il piano del governo sale a 25 miliardi. Gualtieri alla Ue: 'Servono stimoli'|date=11 March 2020|website=la Repubblica|accessdate=12 March 2020}}</ref> In the evening, Conte announced a tightening of the lockdown, with all commercial and retail businesses except those providing essential services, like grocery shops and pharmacies, closed down.<ref name=\":13\" /><ref name=\":12\" /><ref>{{cite web |title=Coronavirus Measures |url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2020/03/11/news/coronavirus_conte_italia_governo_misure-250988471/?ref=RHPPTP-BL-I250988111-C12-P1-S1.12-T1 |website=La Repubblica |date = 11 March 2020|accessdate=11 March 2020}}</ref> He also appointed Domenico Arcuri as Delegated Commissioner for the Emergency. Arcuri will cooperate with Commissioner [[Angelo Borrelli]] with the aim of strengthening the distribution of [[intensive care unit|intensive care]] equipment.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fanpage.it/attualita/coronavirus-il-governo-nominera-domenico-arcuri-commissario-delegato-per-lemergenza/|title=Coronavirus: chi \u00e8 Domenico Arcuri, il commissario delegato per l'emergenza scelto da Conte|website=Fanpage|accessdate=12 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 19 March, the [[Italian Army|Army]] was deployed to the city of [[Bergamo]], the worst hit Italian city by the coronavirus, as the local authorities can no longer process the number of dead residents. The city's mayor [[Giorgio Gori]] said the true number of dead could be much higher than reported.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.adnkronos.com/fatti/cronaca/2020/03/18/coronavirus-gori-tanti-muoiono-casa-non-vengono-contati_tLagSTNm9fczG1a59ZhosI.html|title=Coronavirus, Gori: \"Tanti muoiono in casa, non vengono contati\"|website=Adnkronos}}</ref> Army trucks transported bodies to [[crematorium]]s in several other cities, as cemeteries in the city were full.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.sky.com/story/coronavirus-italian-army-called-in-to-carry-away-corpses-as-citys-crematorium-is-overwhelmed-11959994|title=Coronavirus: Italian army called in as crematorium struggles to cope with deaths|publisher=Sky News}}</ref> On the following day, the Army was called in to assist the police forces in enforcing the lockdown.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Di Donato |first1=Valentina |last2=Ruotolo |first2=Nicola |last3=Smith-Spark |first3=Laura |title=Italy calls in military to enforce lockdown as 627 people die in 24 hours |url=https://edition.cnn.com/2020/03/20/europe/italy-military-coronavirus-intl/index.html |accessdate=21 March 2020 |publisher=CNN |date=20 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 20 March, the Ministry of Health ordered tighter regulations on free movement. The new measures banned open-air sports and running, except individually and in close proximity of one's residence. Parks, playgrounds and public green were closed down. Furthermore, movement across the country was further restricted, by banning \"any movement towards a residence different from the main one\", including holiday homes, during weekends and holidays.<ref>{{cite news |title=Le nuove restrizioni decise dal governo |url=https://www.ilpost.it/2020/03/20/ordinanza-coronavirus-attivita-sportiva-correre/ |accessdate=21 March 2020 |work=Il Post |date=20 March 2020 |language=it-IT}}</ref>\n\nOn 21 March, Conte announced further restrictions within the nationwide lockdown, by halting all non-essential production, industries and businesses in Italy, following the rise in the number of new cases and deaths in the previous days.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Farrer |first1=Martin |title=Italy: PM warns of worst crisis since WW2 as coronavirus deaths leap by almost 800 |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/22/italian-pm-warns-of-worst-crisis-since-ww2-as-coronavirus-deaths-leap-by-almost-800 |accessdate=22 March 2020 |work=The Guardian |date=22 March 2020}}</ref> This measure had also been strongly asked for by multiple institutions, including trade unions, mayors, and regional presidents, as well as medical professionals, but was initially opposed by the industrialists.<ref>{{cite news |title=Coronavirus, i sindaci toscani scrivono a Conte: \"Chiudere tutto ci\u00f2 che non \u00e8 essenziale\" |url=https://www.lanazione.it/cronaca/coronavirus-sindaci-toscana-chiudere-tutto-1.5076824 |accessdate=22 March 2020 |work=La Nazione |date=21 March 2020 |language=it}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title='Chiudere fabbriche', 41 sindaci a Conte \u2013 Abruzzo |url=http://www.ansa.it/abruzzo/notizie/2020/03/17/chiudere-fabbriche-41-sindaci-a-conte_2b8aaf8a-15de-46a2-ae61-5baa6389fb36.html |accessdate=22 March 2020 |work=Agenzia ANSA |date=17 March 2020 |language=it}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Chiudere le fabbriche? La lettera dei sindacati |url=https://www.repubblica.it/economia/2020/03/21/news/chiudere_le_fabbriche_la_lettera_dei_sindacati-251916540/ |accessdate=22 March 2020 |work=la Repubblica |date=21 March 2020 |language=it}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=I medici della Lombardia: \"Chiudere tutte le attivit\u00e0 non essenziali\". Il no degli industriali |url=https://www.huffingtonpost.it/entry/gli-industriali-dicono-no-alla-chiusura-delle-fabbriche_it_5e68d0eec5b60557280e9304 |accessdate=22 March 2020 |work=L'HuffPost |date=11 March 2020 |language=it}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Coronavirus, Milano trema: 634 casi in un giorno. Fontana chiama Conte: chiudere tutto, Esercito per strada |url=https://www.ilmessaggero.it/italia/coronavirus_milano_casi_contagi_lombardia_ultime_notizie-5121166.html |accessdate=22 March 2020 |work=Il Messaggero |language=it}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=De Angelis |first1=Alessandro |title=\"Chiudete tutto, anche le fabbriche\" (di A. De Angelis) |url=https://www.huffingtonpost.it/entry/giorgio-gori-chiudete-tutto-anche-le-fabbriche_it_5e74ad81c5b63c3b648e6263 |accessdate=22 March 2020 |work=L'HuffPost |date=20 March 2020 |language=it}}</ref>\n\nOn 24 March, in a live-streamed press conference, Conte announced a new decree approved by the Council of Ministers. The decree imposed higher fines for the violation of the restrictive measures, and a regulation of the relationship between government and Parliament during the emergency. It included also the possibility of reducing or suspending public and private transport, and gave the regional governments power to impose additional restrictive regulations in their Regions for a maximum of seven days before being confirmed by national decree.<ref>{{cite news |title=Italy announces fines of up to \u20ac3,000 for breaking quarantine rules |url=https://www.thelocal.it/20200324/italy-announces-fines-of-up-to-3000-for-breaking-quarantine-rules |accessdate=25 March 2020 |work=thelocal.it |date=24 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Cosa ha detto Giuseppe Conte |url=https://www.ilpost.it/2020/03/24/decreto-restrizioni-sanzioni-coronavirus/ |accessdate=25 March 2020 |work=Il Post |date=24 March 2020 |language=it-IT}}</ref>\n\nOn 1 April, the government extended the period of lockdown until 13 April, with health minister Speranza saying that the restrictive measures had begun to yield the first positive results.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Henley |first1=Jon |title=Italy extends lockdown amid signs coronavirus infection rate is easing |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/apr/01/italy-extends-lockdown-amid-signs-coronavirus-infection-rate-is-easing |accessdate=1 April 2020 |work=The Guardian |date=1 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 6 April, the government announced a new economic stimulus plan, consisting of \u20ac200 billion of state-guaranteed loans to companies and additional \u20ac200 billion of guarantees to support exports.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Leali |first1=Giorgio |title=Italy adopts \u20ac400B liquidity plan amid coronavirus crisis |url=https://www.politico.eu/article/italy-adopts-e400b-liquidity-plan-amid-coronavirus-crisis/ |accessdate=7 April 2020 |work=POLITICO |date=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 7 April, after more than a month of suspension, the [[Italian Basketball Federation]] officially ended the 2019\u201320 [[Lega Basket Serie A|LBA]] season, without assigning the title.<ref>[https://sportando.basketball/en/italian-basketball-federation-officially-ends-lba-2019-20-season/ Italian Basketball Federation officially ends LBA 2019-20 season], Sportando</ref>\n\nOn 8 April, a government's decree closed all Italian ports until 31 July, stating that they do not ensure the necessary requirements for the classification and definition of \"safe place\", established by the [[Hamburg Rules]]\u00a0on maritime search and rescue.\"<ref>[https://www.huffingtonpost.it/entry/litalia-chiude-i-porti_it_5e8d89f2c5b6e1d10a6c2671?yhj&utm_hp_ref=it-homepage L'Italia chiude i porti], ''Huffington Post''</ref>\n\nOn 10 April, Conte announced the prolongation of the lockdown until 3 May, as well as the reopening of some businesses like bookstores\u00a0and forestry.<ref>[https://www.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/04/10/news/coronavirus_giuseppe_conte_riaperture-253677426/?ref=RHPPTP-BH-I253671889-C12-P2-S2.4-T1 Coronavirus, il premier Conte: \"Chiusura fino al 3 maggio, non possiamo cedere adesso\"]</ref>\n\n===Local measures===\nOn 15 March, President of Campania [[Vincenzo De Luca]] imposed a strict quarantine on [[Ariano Irpino]], in the province of Avellino, and four other municipalities in the province of Salerno, [[Atena Lucana]], [[Caggiano]], [[Polla, Italy|Polla]], and [[Sala Consilina]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Coronavirus, De Luca \"chiude\" altri quattro Comuni |url=https://napoli.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/03/15/news/de_luca_chiude_altri_4_comuni-251388474/ |accessdate=16 March 2020 |work=la Repubblica |date=15 March 2020 |language=it}}</ref>\n\nOn 16 March, President of Emilia-Romagna [[Stefano Bonaccini]] imposed a strengthened quarantine on the municipality of [[Medicina]], near Bologna, since it had developed an intense outbreak. People were not allowed to enter or exit the town for any reason.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://bologna.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/03/16/news/coronavirus_medicina_e_zona_rossa_vietato_entrare_e_uscire-251412467/ |title=Coronavirus, Medicina \u00e8 zona rossa, vietato entrare e uscire|date=16 March 2020|website=la Repubblica}}</ref>\n\n===Screening and testing policies===\n{{Expand section |date=March 2020}}\nThe strategy of mass-testing [[asymptomatic carriers]] was proven to be successful in stopping the spread of the virus in one Italian town.<ref name=Horowitz2020-03-21>{{cite web |last1=Horowitz |first1=Jason |last2=Bubola |first2=Emma |last3=Povoledo |first3=Elisabetta |title=Italy, Pandemic's New Epicenter, Has Lessons for the World |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/03/21/world/europe/italy-coronavirus-center-lessons.html |website=[[The New York Times]] |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20200322023527/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/03/21/world/europe/italy-coronavirus-center-lessons.html |archivedate=23 March 2020 |date=21 March 2020 |url-status=live |quote=steps to isolate the coronavirus and limit people\u2019s movement need to be put in place early, with absolute clarity, then strictly enforced}}</ref><ref name=McCall2020-03-19>{{cite web |last1=McCall |first1=Rosie |title=Coronavirus mass testing experiment in Italian town appears to have halted COVID-19 outbreak |url=https://www.newsweek.com/coronavirus-mass-testing-experiment-italian-town-covid-19-outbreak-1493183 |website=[[Newsweek]] |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20200321131113/https://www.newsweek.com/coronavirus-mass-testing-experiment-italian-town-covid-19-outbreak-1493183 |archivedate=21 March 2020  |date=19 March 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=Crisanti2020-03-20>{{cite web |last1=Crisanti |first1=Andrea |authorlink=Andrea Crisanti (scientist) |last2=Cassone |first2=Antonio |title=In one Italian town, we showed mass testing could eradicate the coronavirus |url=https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2020/mar/20/eradicated-coronavirus-mass-testing-covid-19-italy-vo |website=[[The Guardian]] / [[University of Padua]] |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20200323203803/https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2020/mar/20/eradicated-coronavirus-mass-testing-covid-19-italy-vo |archivedate=23 March 2020 |date=20 March 2020 |url-status=live |quote=asymptomatic or quasi-symptomatic subjects represent a good 70% of all virus-infected people and, still worse, an unknown, yet impossible to ignore portion of them can transmit the virus to others}}</ref> This strategy in Italy was supported by the region of [[Veneto]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ilfattoquotidiano.it/2020/03/18/coronavirus-zaia-vanno-chiusi-supermercati-nel-weekend-e-vietate-passeggiate-si-al-controllo-su-celle-telefoniche-ma-ci-vuole-norma/5740615/|title=Coronavirus, Zaia: \"Vanno chiusi supermercati nel weekend e vietate passeggiate. S\u00ec al controllo su celle telefoniche ma ci vuole norma\"|language=italian|work=[[Il Fatto Quotidiano]]|first= Gisella|last=Ruccia|date=18 March 2020|access-date=23 March 2020|quote=L\u2019esperienza insegna che ogni asintomatico positivo pu\u00f2 contagiare fino a 10 altre persone. Quindi, la caccia all\u2019asintomatico positivo \u00e8 fondamentale, tanto \u00e8 vero che oggi abbiamo 8500 persone in isolamento, letteralmente trovate con questa modalit\u00e0}}</ref>\n\n==Lockdown areas==\n{{main|2020 Italy coronavirus lockdown}}\nOn 22 February, the government established a lockdown for eleven municipalities in [[Lombardy]] and [[Veneto]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.la7.it/nonelarena/video/lelenco-dei-comuni-in-quarantena-a-causa-del-coronavirus-23-02-2020-308963|title=L'elenco dei comuni in quarantena a causa del coronavirus|accessdate=8 March 2020|via=la7.it}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Quarantined areas of LodiProvince.png|thumb|upright=1.36|Map of the ten Lombard municipalities under lockdown since 22 February]]\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" font-size:90%;\"\n|+\nMunicipalities under quarantine, 22 February<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://metro.co.uk/2020/02/25/towns-italy-lockdown-coronavirus-12298246/|title=What towns in Italy are on lockdown because of coronavirus?|date=25 February 2020|work=Metro News|access-date=25 February 2020}}</ref>\n!''Comune''\n!Province\n!Region\n!Population\n|-\n|[[Bertonico]]\n|[[Province of Lodi|Lodi]]\n|[[Lombardy]]\n| style=\"text-align:right;\" |1,118\n|-\n|[[Casalpusterlengo]]\n|[[Province of Lodi|Lodi]]\n|[[Lombardy]]\n| style=\"text-align:right;\" |15,293 \n|-\n|[[Castelgerundo]]\n|[[Province of Lodi|Lodi]]\n|[[Lombardy]]\n| style=\"text-align:right;\" |1,498\n|-\n|[[Castiglione d\u2019Adda]]\n|[[Province of Lodi|Lodi]]\n|[[Lombardy]]\n| style=\"text-align:right;\" |4,646\n|-\n|[[Codogno]]\n|[[Province of Lodi|Lodi]]\n|[[Lombardy]]