le=Diagnosztiz\u00e1lt\u00e1k az \u00f6t\u00f6dik koronav\u00edrus-fert\u0151z\u00f6ttet \u2013 id\u0151s, magyar, beteg f\u00e9rfi|date=7 March 2020|language=hu|accessdate=8 March 2020|via=koronavirus.gov.hu}}</ref>\n\n'''Iceland''' \u2013\nOn 28 February 2020, Iceland confirmed its first case, an Icelandic male in his 50s who had previously been to Northern Italy and was placed in strict [[Isolation (health care)|isolation]] in [[Landsp\u00edtali]] in [[Reykjav\u00edk]].<ref name=\"ruv.is\">{{cite web|url=https://www.ruv.is/frett/fyrsta-tilfelli-covid-19-greint-a-islandi|title=Fyrsta tilfelli COVID-19 greint \u00e1 \u00cdslandi|date=28 February 2020|website=R\u00daV}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://bnonews.com/index.php/2020/02/the-latest-coronavirus-cases/|title=Tracking coronavirus: Map, data and timeline|first=B. N. O.|last=News|date=18 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mbl.is/frettir/innlent/2020/02/28/fyrsta_tilfelli_koronuveiru_greinist_a_islandi/|title=Fyrsta tilfelli k\u00f3r\u00f3nuveiru greinist \u00e1 \u00cdslandi|website=mbl.is|language=is|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref>\nOn 5 March, a total of 34 cases had been confirmed in Iceland, most of which are imported cases from Italy.\n\n'''Ireland''' \u2013\nOn 27 February 2020, Ireland's first case was confirmed by the [[Health Protection Surveillance Centre]]. The male patient had travelled to an affected region in Northern Italy.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rte.ie/news/coronavirus/2020/0229/1119357-coronavirus-ireland/ |title=First case of Covid-19 diagnosed in east of Ireland |date=1 March 2020 |access-date=4 March 2020 |publisher=Raidi\u00f3 Teilif\u00eds \u00c9ireann }}</ref> A second, unrelated case was confirmed on 3 March, a female in the eastern portion of Ireland who had travelled to Italy.<ref>{{cite web|first1=Paul|last1=Cullen|accessdate=3 March 2020|title=Second case of coronavirus is confirmed in east of Ireland|url=https://www.irishtimes.com/news/health/second-case-of-coronavirus-is-confirmed-in-east-of-ireland-1.4191961|website=The Irish Times}}</ref>\n\n'''Latvia''' \u2013\nOn 2 March, Latvia confirmed its first case, a person who had travelled from Milan to Munich and then to [[Riga]] on 29 February.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://eng.lsm.lv/article/society/health/first-case-of-covid-19-coronavirus-confirmed-in-latvia.a350338/|title=First case of COVID-19 coronavirus confirmed in Latvia|website=lsm.lv|access-date=3 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''Lithuania''' \u2013\nOn 28 February, Lithuania confirmed its first case, a 39-year-old woman who arrived in [[Kaunas]] from [[Verona]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.15min.lt/naujiena/aktualu/lietuva/koronavirusas-pasieke-lietuva-uzfiksuotas-pirmasis-atvejis-56-1282110|title=Lietuvoje patvirtintas pirmasis koronaviruso atvejis \u2013 susirgo 39 met\u0173 moteris, atskridusi \u012f Kaun\u0105|website=15min.lt|language=lt|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''Luxembourg''' \u2013\nThe nation's second and fourth cases were persons who had travelled to Italy.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://5minutes.rtl.lu/actu/luxembourg/a/1479054.html|title=RTL 5minutes \u2013 Il revenait d'Italie: Un deuxi\u00e8me cas de coronavirus confirm\u00e9 au Luxembourg|accessdate=8 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://5minutes.rtl.lu/actu/luxembourg/a/1479918.html|title=Sant\u00e9: Un 4e cas de coronavirus valid\u00e9 au Luxembourg|website=5minutes.rtl.lu|accessdate=8 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''Malta''' \u2013\nA 12-year-old Italian brought the infection to Malta.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/world/covid19-malta-first-coronavirus-case-italian-girl-12512852|title=Italian girl becomes Malta's first coronavirus case|website=CNA|accessdate=8 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''Moldova''' \u2013\nOn 7 March, Moldova confirmed its first case, a 48-year-old woman who had returned from Italy.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deschide.md/ro/stiri/social/62248/BREAKING-NEWS-Primul-caz-de-coronavirus-depistat-%C3%AEn-Republica-Moldova-O-femeie-de-48-de-ani-infectat%C4%83.htm|title=BREAKING NEWS// Primul caz de coronavirus depistat \u00een Republica Moldova. O femeie de 48 de ani, infectat\u0103|trans-title=BREAKING NEWS// First coronavirus case detected in Republic of Moldova. A 48-year-old woman, infected|language=ro|website=Deschide.md|date=7 March 2020|access-date=7 March 2020}}</ref> Moldova confirmed the existence of imported case from diseased Italy on 11 March.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://stiri.md/article/incidente/al-patrulea-caz-de-coronavirus-confirmat-in-r-moldova|title=Al patrulea caz de coronavirus, confirmat \u00een R. Moldova|website=stiri.md|accessdate=13 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''Netherlands''' \u2013\nOn 27 February, the Netherlands confirmed its first case, a man who had been in Lombardy and was admitted to Elisabeth-TweeSteden Hospital in [[Tilburg]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rivm.nl/nieuws/patient-met-nieuw-coronavirus-in-nederland|title=Pati\u00ebnt met nieuw coronavirus in Nederland {{!}} RIVM|website=www.rivm.nl|access-date=1 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.telegraaf.nl/nieuws/214089776/rivm-eerste-coronageval-in-nederland|title=RIVM: eerste coronageval in Nederland|date=27 February 2020|website=De Telegraaf|language=nl|access-date=1 March 2020}}</ref>\nOn 28 February, a woman from [[Amsterdam]] who had visited Lombardy was in home isolation in [[Diemen]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rivm.nl/nieuws/tweede-patient-in-nederland-met-covid-19|title=Tweede pati\u00ebnt in Nederland met COVID-19 {{!}} RIVM|website=www.rivm.nl|access-date=1 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''[[North Macedonia]]''' \u2013\nOn 26 February, North Macedonia confirmed its first case, a woman who tested positive at the Clinic for Infectious Diseases, [[Skopje]]. She had stayed in Italy for a month and had been sick for two weeks. Upon returning to North Macedonia, she immediately reported to the clinic.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://vesti.mk/read/article/https%3A%2F%2Freporter.mk%2Fgjuture%2Fpotvrden-prv-sluchaj-od-koronavirus-vo-makedonija%2F|title=\u041f\u043e\u0442\u0432\u0440\u0434\u0435\u043d \u043f\u0440\u0432 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0458 \u043e\u0434 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 \u0432\u043e \u041c\u0430\u043a\u0435\u0434\u043e\u043d\u0438\u0458\u0430 |trans-title=First confirmed case of coronavirus in Macedonia |date=n.d.|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=|language=Macedonian}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://a1on.mk/macedonia/prv-sluchaj-na-zabolen-od-koronavirus-vo-makedonija/|title=\u041f\u0440\u0432 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0458 \u043d\u0430 \u0437\u0430\u0431\u043e\u043b\u0435\u043d \u043e\u0434 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 \u0432\u043e \u041c\u0430\u043a\u0435\u0434\u043e\u043d\u0438\u0458\u0430|date=26 February 2020|website=\u04101\u043e\u043d|access-date=26 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''Norway''' \u2013\nOn 27 February, Norway confirmed that two people who tested positive were linked to the outbreak in Italy. They were quarantined at home in [[Oslo]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fhi.no/nyheter/2020/tre-nye-personer-har-testet-positivt-pa-koronavirus/|title=Tre nye personer har testet positivt p\u00e5 koronavirus|website=Folkehelseinstituttet|language=no|access-date=27 February 2020}}</ref>\nOn 28 February, an individual from Bergen and an employee of [[Oslo University Hospital, Ullev\u00e5l]] tested positive and were placed in home isolation. Both had visited Northern Italy.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nrk.no/vestland/over-hundre-kan-ha-hatt-kontakt-med-koronasmittet-ulleval-ansatt-1.14922358|title=Over hundre kan ha hatt kontakt med koronasmittet Ullev\u00e5l-ansatt|last=Olsson|first=Svein Vestrum|date=28 February 2020|publisher=NRK|language=nb-NO|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fhi.no/nyheter/2020/ytterligere-to-personer-har-testet-positivt-pa-koronavirus/|title=Ytterligere to personer har testet positivt p\u00e5 koronavirus|website=Folkehelseinstituttet|language=no|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref>\nOn 6 March, the Norwegian Institute of Public Health reported that 79 of the 113 confirmed cases in Norway were linked to the outbreak in northern Italy.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fhi.no/en/news/2020/status-coronavirus-friday-6.-mars-2020/|title=Status coronavirus Friday 6. mars 2020|website=Folkehelseinstituttet|date=6 March 2020|access-date=7 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''Poland''' \u2013\nOf the country's first five cases, two were from Italy, two were from Germany and one was from the UK.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://polandin.com/47007012/four-new-coronavirus-cases-confirmed-in-poland|title=Four new coronavirus cases confirmed in Poland|first=Telewizja Polska|last=S.A|website=polandin.com|accessdate=8 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''Portugal''' \u2013\nOn 2 March, a doctor who had travelled to Northern Italy and became ill on 29 February was confirmed positive at Hospital de S\u00e3o Jo\u00e3o in [[Porto]]. On 4 March, a 44-year-old man who had travelled to Italy was confirmed positive at the same hospital.\n\n'''Romania''' \u2013\nOn 26 February, Romania confirmed its first case, a man from [[Gorj County|Gorj]] who tested positive after having come in contact with an 71-year-old man from [[Cattolica]], Italy. The Italian man visited his wife's family and had several business meetings in Romania from 18 to 22 February. The Romanian man was admitted to National Institute of Infectious Diseases Prof. Dr. Matei Bal\u0219 in [[Bucharest]].<ref name=\":5\" /><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hotnews.ro/stiri-sanatate-23687251-primul-caz-infectie-coronavirus-confirmat-oficial-romania.htm|title=ULTIMA OR\u0102 LIVEVIDEOTEXT Primul caz de infec\u021bie cu coronavirus, confirmat oficial \u00een Rom\u00e2nia: Un b\u0103rbat din Gorj care a intrat \u00een contact cu italianul care a vizitat recent \u021bara noastr\u0103 \u2013 Sanatate \u2013 HotNews.ro|date=26 February 2020|website=hotnews.ro|language=ro|access-date=26 February 2020}}</ref>\nOn 28 February, a 45-year-old man from [[Maramure\u0219]] who had returned from Italy on 25 February was admitted to the Clinic of Infectious Diseases and then transferred to [[Cluj County|Cluj]].<ref name=\":9\">{{cite web|url=https://www.digi24.ro/stiri/actualitate/doua-noi-posibile-cazuri-de-coronavirus-in-romania-1267704|title=Dou\u0103 noi cazuri de coronavirus confirmate \u00een Rom\u00e2nia|website=digi24.ro|language=ro|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref> A 38-year-old woman who had returned from Bergamo tested positive was admitted to a hospital in [[Timi\u0219oara]].<ref name=\":9\" />\nOn 3 March, a 47-year-old man who had travelled in the same plane with the 38-year-old woman was confirmed positive and admitted to the same hospital.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.digi24.ro/stiri/actualitate/al-patrulea-caz-de-coronavirus-confirmat-in-romania-1269577|title=Al patrulea caz de coronavirus a fost confirmat \u00een Rom\u00e2nia|trans-title=Fourth coronavirus case was confirmed in Romania|language=ro|website=Digi24|date=3 March 2020|access-date=3 March 2020}}</ref>\nThe majority of confirmed cases in Romania are related to Italy.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.digi24.ro/stiri/actualitate/informatii-oficiale-despre-coronavirus-ministerul-de-interne-26-de-persoane-sunt-in-carantina-2077-sunt-monitorizate-la-domiciliu-1266261|title=Coronavirus Rom\u00e2nia, INFORMA\u021aII OFICIALE: 36 de persoane au fost infectate. Primul medic confirmat cu COVID-19|trans-title=Coronavirus Romania, OFFICIAL INFORMATION: 36 people got infected. First medic infected with COVID-19|language=ro|website=Digi24|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|date=11 March 2020|access-date=11 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''Russia''' \u2013\nOn 2 March, a Russian citizen who had returned from Italy was diagnosed.<ref>{{cite news |title=Russian citizen who returned from Italy diagnosed with coronavirus: RIA cites ministry |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-russia/russian-citizen-who-returned-from-italy-diagnosed-with-coronavirus-ria-cites-ministry-idUSKBN20P1JH |accessdate=4 March 2020 |agency=Reuters |date=2 March 2020 }}</ref>\n\n'''San Marino''' \u2013\nOn 27 February, San Marino confirmed its first case, an 88-year-old man with pre-existing medical conditions who was hospitalised at Rimini Hospital.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.altarimini.it/News132152-coronavirus-primo-caso-nella-repubblica-di-san-marino.php|title=Coronavirus: primo caso nella Repubblica di San Marino|date=27 February 2020|website=Altarimini.it|language=it|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.libertas.sm/notizie/2020/02/27/coronavirus-primo-caso-a-san-marino-attivati-i-protocolli-sanitari.html|title=Coronavirus: primo caso a San Marino. Attivati i protocolli sanitari.|last=webit.it|last2=Libertas|website=Libertas|language=it|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''Serbia''' \u2013\nOn 6 March, Serbia registered its first case, a 43-year-old man who had been to Budapest and Italy. At least one other case had been to Italy.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/serbian/lat/srbija-51831539|title=Korona virus: Potvr\u0111eno \u0161est novih slu\u010dajeva u Srbiji|newspaper=BBC News Na Srpskom|date=11 March 2020|accessdate=12 March 2020|via=bbc.com}}</ref>\n\n'''Slovakia''' \u2013\nAn asymptomatic man who had travelled to Venice between 14 and 15 February transmitted the virus to his father and his wife.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://spectator.sme.sk/c/22352401/three-coronavirus-cases-in-slovakia.html|title=Three coronavirus cases confirmed in Slovakia|first=Petit Press|last=a.s|date=7 March 2020|website=spectator.sme.sk|accessdate=8 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''Slovenia''' \u2013\nMany Slovenian cases are linked to Italy, including the nation's first case.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.24ur.com/novice/slovenija/epidemiologi-iscejo-vse-s-katerimi-je-imel-okuzeni-slovenec-stike.html|title=Oku\u017ebo s koronavirusom potrdili \u017ee pri \u0161estih osebah, ne gre samo za motoriste iz Maroka|website=24ur.com|accessdate=8 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''Spain''' \u2013\nOn 24 February, a 69-year-old medical doctor from Lombardy who had been vacationing in [[Tenerife]] since 17 February tested positive at the [[Hospital Universitario Nuestra Se\u00f1ora de Candelaria|University Hospital of the Nuestra Se\u00f1ora de Candelaria]]. A 25-year-old man returning from a holiday in Italy also tested positive in [[Asturias]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/24/news/coronavirus_italiano_positivo_al_test_a_tenerife_e_il_terzo_caso_di_contagio_in_spagna-249508945/|title=Turista italiano positivo al test a Tenerife. Primo caso sospetto nelle Asturie: \u00e8 un giovane di ritorno dall'Italia|date=24 February 2020|website=la Repubblica|language=it|access-date=24 February 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Repubblica_25Feb_Tenerife\">{{cite web|url=https://www.repubblica.it/esteri/2020/02/25/news/coronavirus_contagiati_in_italia-249569108/|title=Coronavirus, positivi due italiani a Tenerife. Mille persone nell'hotel in quarantena|date=25 February 2020|website=la Repubblica|language=it|access-date=25 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rtve.es/noticias/20200224/italiano-da-positivo-coronavirus-sur-tenerife/2004321.shtml|title=Un italiano da positivo por coronavirus en el sur de Tenerife|last=RTVE.es/AGENCIAS|date=24 February 2020|website=RTVE.es|language=es|access-date=25 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/feb/25/tenerife-coronavirus-guests-hotel-quarantined|title=Tenerife coronavirus: 1,000 guests at hotel quarantined|date=25 February 2020|website=The Guardian|access-date=26 February 2020}}</ref>\nOn 25 February, the wife of the doctor from Lombardy tested positive and was admitted to the same hospital where her husband was being treated.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://diariodeavisos.elespanol.com/2020/02/un-ciudadano-italiano-da-positivo-en-coronavirus-en-el-sur-de-tenerife/|title=Un ciudadano italiano da positivo en el sur de Tenerife por coronavirus|last=Guti\u00e9rrez|first=Juan Jes\u00fas|date=25 February 2020|website=Diario de Avisos|language=es-ES|access-date=27 February 2020}}</ref> A 36-year-old Italian woman living in [[Barcelona]] who had visited Bergamo and Milan from 12 to 22 February also tested positive.<ref name=\"Repubblica_25Feb_Europe\" /><ref name=\"Repubblica_25Feb_Tenerife\" /><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.thelocal.es/20200225/woman-in-barcelona-tests-positive-to-coronavirus-the-first-confirmed-case-in-mainland-spain|title=Woman in Barcelona tests positive to coronavirus, the first confirmed case on mainland Spain|date=25 February 2020|work=thelocal.es|accessdate=26 February 2020}}</ref> A man from [[Villarreal]] who had recently travelled to Milan tested positive and was admitted to Hospital Universitario de La Plana.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.levante-emv.com/comunitat-valenciana/2020/02/25/coronavirus-caso-valencia-positivo/1982275.html|title=Sanidad confirma el primer caso de coronavirus en la C. Valenciana|last=Levante-EMV|website=levante-emv.com|language=es|access-date=26 February 2020}}</ref> A 24-year-old man from [[Madrid]] who had recently returned from Northern Italy tested positive and was admitted to [[Hospital Carlos III]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.levante-emv.com/espana/2020/02/25/confirmado-primer-caso-coronavirus-cataluna/1982130.html|title=Un caso de coronavirus en Madrid eleva a siete los infectados en Espa\u00f1a|last=Levante-EMV|website=levante-emv.com|language=es|access-date=26 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.telemadrid.es/noticias/madrid/Confirmado-primer-caso-coronavirus-Madrid-0-2207779217--20200225111539.html|title=Confirmado el primer caso de coronavirus en Madrid|date=25 February 2020|work=telemadrid.es|accessdate=26 February 2020|language=es}}</ref>\nOn 26 February, two Italian tourists who were vacationing with the Lombardy doctor and his wife also tested positive. The group were transferred to University Hospital of the Nuestra Se\u00f1ora de Candelaria and underwent quarantine.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rtve.es/noticias/20200226/dos-nuevos-positivos-coronavirus-entre-italianos-del-hotel-adeje-canarias/2004660.shtml|title=Dos nuevos positivos por coronavirus entre los italianos del hotel de Adeje de Canarias|last=EFE|first=RTVE es /|date=26 February 2020|website=RTVE.es|language=es|access-date=26 February 2020}}</ref> A 22-year-old man from Barcelona who travelled to Milan between 22 and 25 February tested positive and was admitted to Hospital Cl\u00ednic.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ara.cat/societat/segon-cas-coronavirus-catalunya-noi-22-anys-italia_0_2406359478.html|title=Un noi de 22 anys que havia viatjat a Mil\u00e0 \u00e9s el segon cas de coronavirus a Catalunya|last=Bassas|first=Antoni|date=26 February 2020|website=Ara.cat|language=ca-ES|access-date=27 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vilaweb.cat/noticies/almenys-setze-infectats-per-coronavirus-i-250-persones-en-quarantena-al-nord-ditalia/|title=[EN DIRECTE] Confirmat un segon cas de coronavirus a Catalunya|website=VilaWeb|language=ca|access-date=27 February 2020}}</ref> A woman from [[La Gomera]] who travelled to Italy between 4 and 8 February tested positive and was admitted to Hospital General de La Gomera in Tenerife.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.20minutos.es/noticia/4166583/0/nuevo-positivo-gomera-eleva-11-numero-infectados-coronavirus-espana/|title=Un nuevo positivo en La Gomera eleva a 11 el n\u00famero de infectados por coronavirus en Espa\u00f1a|last=20minutos|date=26 February 2020|website=20minutos.es \u2013 \u00daltimas Noticias|language=es|access-date=27 February 2020}}</ref>\nOn 27 February, a 44-year-old man from [[Valencia]] who worked as a sportswriter and had travelled to Milan's [[San Siro]] Stadium on 19 February to watch a football game tested positive and was admitted to Hospital Cl\u00ednico [[University of Valencia|Universitario de Val\u00e8ncia]]. Two other people with whom he had made contact also tested positive and were admitted to the same hospital. Two more people who had visited the same football game in Milan were hospitalised at the same place.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Linde|first=Pablo|url=https://elpais.com/sociedad/2020/01/31/actualidad/1580509404_469734.html|title=Sanidad confirma en La Gomera el primer caso de coronavirus en Espa\u00f1a|date=1 February 2020|work=El Pa\u00eds|access-date=27 February 2020|language=es|issn=1134-6582}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://en.as.com/en/2020/02/27/football/1582794092_036585.html|title=Valencia fan in Milan last week for UCL tie tests positive for coronavirus|date=27 February 2020|website=AS.com|access-date=27 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last=Bono|first=Ferran|url=https://elpais.com/sociedad/2020/02/27/actualidad/1582795523_075914.html|title=Un periodista que viaj\u00f3 a Mil\u00e1n para cubrir el Valencia-Atalanta, positivo por coronavirus|date=27 February 2020|work=El Pa\u00eds|access-date=27 February 2020|language=es|issn=1134-6582}}</ref><ref name=\":6\">{{cite web|url=https://www.levante-emv.com/comunitat-valenciana/2020/02/27/coronavirus-valencia-nuevos-casos-infectados/1983062.html|title=Sanidad confirma 6 nuevos casos de coronavirus en la C. Valenciana|last=Levante-EMV|website=levante-emv.com|language=es|access-date=27 February 2020}}</ref> A woman who had visited Milan was hospitalised at Hospital de Sagunto, Valencia.<ref name=\":6\" /> An Italian student studying in Valencia who had visited Northern Italy was admitted to Hospital Universitario Doctor Peset.<ref name=\":6\" /> A 22-year-old woman from Tenerife who had travelled to Italy from 19 to 25 February was admitted to Hospital Cl\u00ednic.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.abc.es/espana/catalunya/abci-mujer-22-anos-viajo-italia-tercer-caso-importado-coronavirus-cataluna-202002271249_noticia.html|title=Una tinerfe\u00f1a de 22 a\u00f1os que viaj\u00f3 a Italia, tercer caso \"importado\" de coronavirus en Catalu\u00f1a|date=27 February 2020|website=abc|language=es|access-date=27 February 2020}}</ref> An 18-year-old Italian student studying at IE University, [[Segovia]], who had just returned from Milan, was admitted to Hospital General de Segovia.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.elnortedecastilla.es/segovia/ingresado-joven-habitaciones-20200227182120-nt.html|title=Un alumno italiano de IE University en Segovia, primer caso positivo de coronavirus en la regi\u00f3n|date=27 February 2020|website=El Norte de Castilla|language=es|access-date=27 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.leonoticias.com/castillayleon/primer-coronavirus-castilla-20200227184850-nt.html|title=Confirmados en Segovia y Valladolid los dos primeros casos registrados en Castilla y Le\u00f3n|date=27 February 2020|website=Leonoticias|language=es|access-date=27 February 2020}}</ref>\nOn 28 February, a 27-year-old man from [[Aragon]] with a history of recent trips to Milan tested positive.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.elespanol.com/ciencia/salud/|title=Noticias sobre Salud y Medicina en EL ESPA\u00d1OL|website=El Espa\u00f1ol|language=es-ES|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''Sweden''' \u2013\nOn 26 February, Sweden confirmed that a 30-year-old man who previously visited Northern Italy fell ill three days after returning to Sweden and was admitted to [[Sahlgrenska University Hospital]] in [[Gothenburg]].<ref>{{Cite news|last=Bolin|first=Mattias|url=https://www.svt.se/nyheter/lokalt/vast/bekraftat-coronafall-i-goteborg-person-vardas-pa-sahlgrenska|title=Bekr\u00e4ftat coronafall i G\u00f6teborg \u2013 person v\u00e5rdas p\u00e5 Sahlgrenska|date=26 February 2020|work=SVT Nyheter|access-date=26 February 2020|language=sv}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.expressen.se/gt/en-person-i-goteborg-har-testats-positivt-for-corona/|title=Bekr\u00e4ftat fall av Coronavirus i G\u00f6teborg \u2013 personen har varit i Italien|last=Ekstr\u00f6m|first=reas|website=Expressen|language=sv|access-date=26 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.folkhalsomyndigheten.se/nyheter-och-press/nyhetsarkiv/2020/februari/nytt-bekraftat-fall-av-covid-19/|title=Nytt bekr\u00e4ftat fall av covid-19 \u2013 Folkh\u00e4lsomyndigheten|website=folkhalsomyndigheten.se|language=sv|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref>\nOn 27 February, three patients in their 30s were confirmed positive in [[V\u00e4stra G\u00f6taland County|V\u00e4stra G\u00f6taland]]. Two of them had been in contact with the Gothenburg patient, while the other had previously visited Italy.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.folkhalsomyndigheten.se/nyheter-och-press/nyhetsarkiv/2020/februari/ytterligare-fall-av-covid-19-i-flera-regioner/|title=Ytterligare fall av covid-19 i flera regioner \u2013 Folkh\u00e4lsomyndigheten|website=folkhalsomyndigheten.se|language=sv|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.cision.com/se/vastra-gotalandsregionen/r/tre-nya-bekraftade-fall-av-coronavirusinfektion--covid-19--i-vastra-gotaland,c3048641|title=Tre nya bekr\u00e4ftade fall av coronavirusinfektion (Covid-19) i V\u00e4stra G\u00f6taland|website=News Powered by Cision|language=sv|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref><ref name=\":18\">{{cite web|url=https://www.thelocal.se/20200227/five-new-cases-of-the-coronavirus-in-sweden|title=Sweden confirms five new coronavirus cases, including first patient in Stockholm|last=L\u00f6fgren|first=Emma|date=27 February 2020|website=thelocal.se|publisher=The Local|accessdate=27 February 2020}}</ref>\nOn 28 February, a man in his 50s who had returned from Northern Italy on 24 February tested positive and was admitted to a hospital in [[J\u00f6nk\u00f6ping]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rjl.se/nyheter/nyheter-och-pressmeddelanden/pressmeddelande-28-februari-2020-ytterligare-bekraftat-fall-i-jonkopings-lan-av-nya-coronaviruset-covid-19--45553|title=Pressmeddelande 28 februari 2020: Ytterligare bekr\u00e4ftat fall i J\u00f6nk\u00f6pings l\u00e4n av nya coronaviruset (covid-19), Region J\u00f6nk\u00f6pings l\u00e4n|website=rjl.se|language=sv|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''Switzerland''' \u2013\nOn 25 February, Switzerland confirmed its first case, a 70-year-old man in the canton of [[Canton of Ticino|Ticino]] who had previously visited Milan.<ref name=\"Repubblica_25Feb_Tenerife\" /><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-switzerland-coronavirus-idUSKBN20J1ZO|title=Swiss authorities confirm first case of coronavirus|date=25 February 2020|agency=Reuters|access-date=26 February 2020}}</ref>\nOn 27 February, a 28-year-old IT worker from [[Geneva]] who had recently returned from Milan tested positive and was admitted to [[Geneva University Hospitals|Geneva University Hospital]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bag.admin.ch/bag/en/home/das-bag/aktuell/medienmitteilungen.msg-id-78268.html|title=New coronavirus Covid-19: three new confirmed cases in Switzerland|website=bag.admin.ch|access-date=27 February 2020}}</ref><ref name=\":02\">{{cite web|url=https://www.swissinfo.ch/eng/politics/covid-19_switzerland-confirms-second-coronavirus-case/45582788|title=Switzerland confirms total of four coronavirus cases|last=swissinfo.ch|first=S. W. I.|last2=Corporation|first2=a branch of the Swiss Broadcasting|website=SWI swissinfo.ch|access-date=27 February 2020}}</ref> Two Italian children on vacation in [[Canton of Grisons|Graub\u00fcnden]] tested positive and were hospitalised.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gr.ch/DE/institutionen/verwaltung/djsg/ga/coronavirus/Seiten/Info.aspx|title=Informationen zum Coronavirus|website=gr.ch|access-date=27 February 2020}}</ref><ref name=\":02\" /><ref name=\":92\">{{cite web|url=https://www.bielertagblatt.ch/nachrichten/schweiz/graubuenden-sagt-den-engadiner-skimarathon-ab|title=Graub\u00fcnden sagt den Engadiner Skimarathon ab|website=Bieler Tagblatt|language=de|access-date=27 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227174547/https://www.bielertagblatt.ch/nachrichten/schweiz/graubuenden-sagt-den-engadiner-skimarathon-ab|archive-date=27 February 2020|url-status=dead}}</ref> A 26-year-old man in [[Canton of Aargau|Aargau]] who had visited Verona on a business trip the previous week tested positive and was hospitalised.<ref name=\":02\" /> A 30-year-old woman who visited Milan was admitted to a hospital in [[Z\u00fcrich|Zurich]].<ref name=\":02\" /> A young woman who had travelled to Milan tested positive in [[Canton of Basel-Stadt|Basel-City]]. She worked for a daycare centre in [[Riehen]], and after her test was confirmed, the children at the daycare were put into a two-week quarantine.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-swiss-idUSKCN20L167|title=Swiss coronavirus cases rise to nine as children placed in precautionary quarantine|date=27 February 2020|agency=Reuters|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref> On 28 February, her partner, a 23-year-old man, also tested positive in [[Canton of Basel-Landschaft|Basel-Country]].<ref name=\":21\">{{cite web|url=https://www.rts.ch/info/suisse/11127000-manifestations-d-ampleur-interdites-en-raison-du-coronavirus-conference-de-presse-du-conseil-federal-en-direct.html|title=Les manifestations d'ampleur interdites en Suisse en raison du coronavirus|date=28 February 2020|website=rts.ch|language=fr|access-date=1 March 2020}}</ref> On 29 February, the man's mother tested positive as well. \nOn 28 February, a 45-year-old-man who had travelled to Milan tested positive in [[Z\u00fcrich]].<ref name=\":21\" />\n\n'''Ukraine''' \u2013\nOn 3 March, Ukraine confirmed its first case in [[Chernivtsi]], a man who had travelled from Italy by plane to the Romanian city of [[Suceava]] and then to Ukraine by car with his wife.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/katyagorchinskaya/2020/03/03/first-case-of-coronavirus-registered-in-ukraine/|title=First Case Of Coronavirus Registered in Ukraine|date=3 March 2020|access-date=3 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''United Kingdom''' \u2013\nOn 27 February, the United Kingdom confirmed that a patient who had visited Milan tested positive and was admitted to [[Royal Free Hospital]] in London.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-51656609|title=Two more coronavirus cases confirmed in England|date=27 February 2020|work=BBC News|access-date=27 February 2020}}</ref> Northern Ireland reported its first case, an adult who had travelled from Northern Italy via Dublin and was admitted to Royal Victoria Hospital in [[Belfast]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Kearney|first=Vincent|date=27 February 2020|title=NI coronavirus case had travelled through Dublin|url=https://www.rte.ie/news/health/2020/0227/1117991-ireland-coronavirus/}}</ref>\nOn 28 February, Wales reported its first case, a patient who had returned from northern Italy was treated at a specialist unit in England.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-wales-51450517|title=First case of coronavirus in Wales confirmed|date=28 February 2020|work=BBC News|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Oceania===\n\n'''Australia''' \u2013\nAt least one case has travel history to Italy.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.health.gov.au/news/health-alerts/novel-coronavirus-2019-ncov-health-alert|title=Coronavirus (COVID-19) health alert|first=Australian Government Department of|last=Health|date=6 February 2020|website=Australian Government Department of Health|accessdate=8 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''New Zealand''' \u2013\nOn 4 March, the New Zealand Ministry of Health confirmed its second case, a woman in her 30s who returned to [[Auckland]] from Northern Italy.<ref>{{cite news |title=Second Case of COVID-19 Confirmed in NZ |url=https://www.health.govt.nz/news-media/media-releases/second-case-covid-19-confirmed-nz |accessdate=4 March 2020 |work=Ministry of Health NZ }}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n{{Portal bar|COVID-19|Italy|Current events|Medicine|Viruses}}\n* [[:Template:2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic articles]]<!-- Template will not display if transcluded, since it causes the page to exceed the Post-expand include size -->\n* [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in San Marino]]\n* [[Timeline of the 2019\u20132020 coronavirus pandemic in March 2020]]\n* [[2020 coronavirus pandemic on cruise ships]]\n* [[Pandemic]]\n* [[Epidemiology of COVID-19]]\n* [[2009 flu pandemic in Europe]]\n* [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Europe]]\n* [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in France]]\n* [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Germany]]\n* [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Malta]]\n* [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Spain]]\n* [[List of epidemics]]\n* [[Coronavirus disease 2019]]\n* [[Coronavirus disease]]s, a group of closely related syndromes\n* [[Severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2]]\n* [[Severe acute respiratory syndrome-related coronavirus]]\n* [[Contact tracing]], inquiry opened immediately to identify and contact everyone who has been in close contact with an infected person and subsequent collection of further information about these contacts\n\n==References==\n<references /><!-- Do not replace with {{reflist}}, since that would hide references if the Post-expand include size of the page is exceeded -->\n\n==External links==\n* {{cite web |url = http://www.salute.gov.it/nuovocoronavirus |publisher=[[Ministry of Health (Italy)|Ministero della Salute]] |title=Official website|language=italian}}\n* {{cite web | url = http://opendatadpc.maps.arcgis.com/apps/opsdashboard/index.html#/b0c68bce2cce478eaac82fe38d4138b1 | title = Geomap and open data on the diffusion of COVID-19 in Italy | website = [[Protezione Civile]] | archive-url = http://archive.is/wip/fViDD | archive-date = 12 March 2020 | url-status = live}} (desktop version)\n* {{cite web |url=https://coronavirus-global.com/italy |title=Coronaviru