SORT:Powerpuff Girls (2016 TV series) episodes, List of}}\n[[Category:2010s television-related lists]]\n[[Category:Cartoon Network-related lists]]\n[[Category:Lists of American children's animated television series episodes]]\n[[Category:The Powerpuff Girls|2016 episodes]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n{{DISPLAYTITLE:List of ''The Powerpuff Girls'' (2016 TV series) episodes}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=December 2016}}\n[[File:The Powerpuff Girls (2016) reboot logo.svg|frameless|right]]\n''[[The Powerpuff Girls (2016 TV series)|The Powerpuff Girls]]'' is an [[United States|American]] [[animated television series]] based on the original [[The Powerpuff Girls|1998 series]] by [[Craig McCracken]], which is directed by [[Nick Jennings (artist)|Nick Jennings]] and [[Bob Boyle (animator)|Bob Boyle]]. The series premiered on April 4, 2016. Voice actor [[Natalie Palamides]] announced that the show was renewed for a second season that premiered on March 3, 2017 with the series first 22-minute special, \"The Last Donnycorn\".<ref>{{cite web|last=Vilas-Boas|first=Eric|url=https://medium.com/the-dot-and-line/exclusive-interview-natalie-palamides-on-buttercup-and-powerpuff-girls-season-2-8caab6293971|title=Exclusive Interview: Natalie Palamides on Buttercup and ''Powerpuff Girls'' Season 2|work=The Dot and Line|publisher=Medium|date=May 26, 2016|accessdate=May 27, 2016}}</ref>\n\n{{As of|2019|6|16|df=US}}, 122 episodes of the series have aired, currently airing the third season.\n\n==Series overview==\n<onlyinclude>{{Series overview\n|color1=9FDFDF\n|color2=DF9F9F\n|color3=C8A2C8\n|color10A=9FDF9F\n|color10B=F4A460\n|color10S=DFDF9F\n|end1={{End date|2016|12|1}}\n|end2={{End date|2018|5|13}}\n|end3=<!-- TBA -->\n|end10A={{End date|2016|6|24}}\n|end10B={{End date|2017|9|18}}\n|episodes1=39<ref>HaleyMancini, (January 31, 2017). [https://twitter.com/HaleyMancini/status/826534327265619969?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw \"New eps will be airing in the spring! Sorry, w